title: cheese-frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves; trim base from cauliflower.
Wash.
Precook whole in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble into small pieces.
In a separate small bowl, blend together the mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli salad.
Marinate the salad in dressing at least 1 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 4.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and 1/2 c. cheese.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.
Cover with remaining cheese and cooked bacon.
Return to oven until cheese is melted. Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Serve with biscuits or toast.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Sift
together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and blend.
Beat
shortening
until
creamy
(300 strokes or 2 minutes at medium
speed).
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. After each addition,
add
eggs and beat until thick. Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, blending thoroughly after
each addition.
Fold
in
fruits
and
raisins.
Grease bottom only of 4 1/2 x
1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Remove
from
pan.
Cool
thoroughly
before slicing.
Freezes well.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons of margarine in small saucepan, stirring constantly and cool. Blend remaining butter with cream cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: hot burger potato baskets
directions: Combine beef and seasoned salt, shape into 4 oval patties 2 inches thick.
Broil or fry until done.
Prepare brown gravy according to package directions, keep warm.
Cut lengthwise slit across top of potato.
Gently squeeze into circular shape.
With a spoon press pulp against potato skin to form a basket.
Sprinkle with additional seasoned salt.
Place meat patties in potato baskets.
Top with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Serve topped with gravy.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil for 1 hour.
Saute vegetables and herbs in oil and add to pot.
Simmer until tender, about 2 to 3 hours.
If you want them creamier, remove 1 cup beans, mash or cream in blender and return to pot.

title: baked haddock
directions: Add milk and salt in a bowl.
Dip fish in milk; dip in crushed crackers.
Line pan with tinfoil.
Place fish in pan; sprinkle with spices.
Pour melted butter on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove top foil; bake 15 minutes more.

title: dump cake
directions: In bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, mix pineapple and pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of fruit.
Cut margarine into pats and spread out rather evenly on cake mix.
Top with nuts and/or coconut.
(A cinnamon/sugar mix is good with apple.)
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold.

title: dinner saladgroves, texas
directions: Layer in platter lettuce, Water Chestnuts and tuna.

title: pumpernickel bread with dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, except bread.
Cut a hole in the top of the loaf of bread; hollow out the loaf, saving bread chunks to dip in the finished dip.
Chill dip prior to serving.
Place dip inside of bread loaf and surround the loaf with bread chunks for dipping.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Dip sliced eggplant in beaten egg; shake off excess, then shake in bag with bread crumbs.
Place on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a liberal coating of Salad Supreme.
Spray tops of eggplant slices with Pam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle slices with grated Parmesan; bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased loaf cake pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake with fork while still hot.

title: rugalees
directions: Cream 2 sticks of oleo with 1 cup sour cream.
Add 2 cups flour.
Separate dough into four balls and refrigerate an hour or two.
Roll each ball out into a circle.
Brush with vegetable oil. Sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts.
Cut into triangles; add a dab of apple jelly and roll up.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.
(Roll from outside edge of circle toward center.)

title: judy's 3-step cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese thaw at room temperature.
Mix cheese, milk and lemon juice together in glass bowl.
Mix until all lumps are gone.
Pour into pie shell.
Let sit for 4 hours or overnight is best.
Add toppings to your taste.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk and crushed wafers.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat or in microwave, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine.
Mix well.
Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips over crust; top with caramel mixture, spreading to edge of pan.
Top with spoonfuls of remaining cake mixture and press gently into caramel.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in a saucepan.
Cook until melted.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cream cheese until soft and add hot mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts and chill until almost set.
Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Pour into oblong dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Glycerin will make bubbles iridescent. Blow bubbles through wire loops or spools.
To make lots of bubbles outdoors, place fly swatter in soapy water and swing it around.

title: hearty goulash soup
directions: Brown beef shanks in heated oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven. Remove and reserve shanks as they brown.
When all are browned, discard drippings.
Add butter to pan; in it cook onions over medium heat until limp and lightly browned.
Mix in garlic and paprika.
Add beef shanks (and any juices), water, red and green peppers, salt, caraway seed, chile and tomatoes (coarsely chopped, with liquid).
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread out the rolls on a cookie sheet, pressing together, and bake until lightly browned.

title: mom's potatoes
directions: Place hash browns, half and half, butter, chives and salt and pepper to taste in large pot over medium heat. Stir until consistency of pudding. Reduce heat after thawing begins
to avoid scorching. Place potato mixture in a greased 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake, loosely covered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Makes a lot and can easily be cut in half.
Recipe serves 10 to 12.
Preparation time: 45 minutes.
Cooking time:
45 minutes.
Can be made up ahead of time.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cheese in 1-quart casserole in microwave oven for 1 minute.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except crab.
Stir in crab. Cook in microwave oven for 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove, stir and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon paprika and serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk in a large bowl and refrigerate 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate overnight. Do not attempt to mold.

title: sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients except club soda.
Peel orange from top to bottom without interruption leaving bottom of peel attached.
Suspend orange in Sangria and let stand at least 1 hour before serving.
Add club soda just before guests arrive.

title: chicken breasts floretine
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft. Combine with all ingredients listed above except chicken.
Mix well; season liberally.
Trim fat of chicken.
Loosen skin from one side and stuff with approximately 1/3 cup of filling.
Tuck the skin under the breast, forming a round dome shape.
Place in a buttered Pyrex dish. Preheat oven.
Bake breasts at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Do not overcook.
Cool slightly before serving. This can be sliced into smaller serving pieces.
Serves 6.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Add margarine and mix thoroughly.
(If dough seems dry, work with hands.)
Mold dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked gold(carrots)
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Brown onion in bacon fat; drain.
Stir carrots, crumbled bacon, onion and brown sugar together.
Pour melted butter over mixture and bake, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed and heated through.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack. Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: monterey meat roll
directions: Combine tomato sauce, paste and 1/2 teaspoon oregano in small bowl.
Set aside.
Assemble and attach food grinder using fine grinding plate.
Turn to speed 4 and grind beef, veal, pork and onion into bowl.
Add bread crumbs, egg, remaining oregano, salt, pepper and 1/2 of tomato mixture into bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
Turn to speed 2 and mix 1 minute.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients a few seconds. (In blender, press on button and then off.) Ready to eat. Yield: 1 quart.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt margarine; add onions and celery.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add
salt,
pepper,
cayenne,
mustard
and Worcestershire
sauce.
Then
add
milk and diced bread.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Cool and let stand.
In a large bowl, add hard-boiled
eggs,
crab
meat, dash of salt, parsley and onion and mix.
Then add to cooled bread mixture and refrigerate
until cooled.
Make balls and shape.
Dip in flour, then egg and breadcrumbs.
Fry in deep fat for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: rice krispie chicken
directions: Melt oleo, add salt and pepper. Stir. Crush rice krispies. Dip chicken in oleo and then in rice krispies. Place in shallow pan, skin side up. Bake at 375° about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheesy fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter on medium heat, stirring continually. Pour liquid over sifted 10x and cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham loaves
directions: Mix ingredients well and make into individual loaves.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Spoon sauce over before baking and two times during.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saute butter, flour and onions.
Add parsley, half and half, crabmeat and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add sherry, pepper and salt.
Serve with crackers as a dip or thicken a little more and use as main dish.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, cauliflower, onion, carrots and celery. Put peas in strainer and run under hot water.
Add peas to salad and mix.
Put half of salad in serving bowl.
Layer mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar on top.
Add layer of 1/2 of the bacon and 1 cup of shredded cheese.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese.
Repeat for 2 layers. Refrigerate.
Mix well before serving.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle in dry Jell-O. Fold in oranges and pineapple.

title: i love this guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash with fork.
Blend in picante sauce, garlic and salt.
Add tomatoes, onion and lemon juice.
May be served as a dip or on a head of lettuce as a salad.

title: "veggie" pizza(great for the summer)
directions: Spread rolls in cookie sheet and press to cover bottom of pan. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook on low temperature about 2 hours.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake in 475° oven for 5 minutes.
Turn oven down to 425° and finish baking for about 15 minutes or until your knife comes out clean.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes.
Pour into a casserole; top with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly.

title: stuffed bread
directions: You will need; rolling pin, wooden toothpicks, nonstick spray, baking sheet, cooling rack Drain pepper salad well Roll dough out into a rectangular shape Layer ham, cheese, salami, and peppers onto the dough Roll the bread over onto itself. Pinch lengthwise and ends, secure with toothpicks Bake about 20 minutes at 400F Cut in half (to drain juices) and set on cooling rack over a sink or pan. Serve warm or cold. Can be frozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into crusts.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: ruthie's salad dressing
directions: Mix soup and oil in mixer and blend in other ingredients and bottle.
Enjoy.

title: chinese wings
directions: Cut off wing tips and discard.
Cut each wing into 2 sections.
In a shallow glass or ceramic bowl, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Add chicken wings and marinate several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove wings from marinade (reserve marinade) and place in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Cook in 325° oven for about 15 minutes. Cook wings an additional 15 minutes, basting with marinade and turn them over.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Baste with honey just before removing from oven.

title: evelyn's cheese cake supreme
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter.
Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan 2 1/4-inch deep and press mixture onto bottom.
Let ingredients except last two, reach room temperature.
Then beat cheese until fluffy.
Mix sugar and flour; gradually blend into cheese, keeping mixture smooth.
Add grated rinds, then eggs and yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in cream. Turn into crust and bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 200° and bake 1 hour more.
Remove from heat and cool away from drafts. Refrigerate until cold and remove sides of pan.
Top with glaze and fruit.
Refrigerate.
Cake may be made a day ahead, but glaze on day served.

title: spaghetti  pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. (Should have 3 cups.)
Stir butter into hot pasta.
Stir in Parmesan and eggs.
Place spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.

title: busy day individual meat loaves
directions: Crumble beef into large bowl.
Add salt.
Sprinkle with crumbs and milk.
Let stand a few minutes until crumbs are soft. Blend together.
Mix in egg, onion, sage, thyme, nutmeg and black pepper, mixing well.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet, about 3-inches apart.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, ginger, garlic salt (if used), soy sauce and mustard.
Spread mixture over tops of loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with green pepper before serving.
Good served with baked potatoes, green salad and your favorite beverage.

title: mo's screech treats
directions: *Suggest raisins, apples, nuts, peaches, strawberries and/or raspberries, dates and bananas.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles per directions on package for baking in oven. Combine mushroom soup, milk and Cheddar cheese.
(Save some cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.)
Heat until cheese melts on low heat.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip and yogurt.
Slice in fresh fruit.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra in hot jars.
Add dill seed, pepper and garlic. Bring vinegar and salt to boil. Pour over okra and seal jars. Okay to eat in 6 weeks.

title: cheddar turkey casserole
directions: Prepare rice. Add onion.
Put in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with peas. Add turkey.
Mix soup and milk; pour over rice and turkey. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: liver and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups boiling water for 5 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.
Brown onion in butter and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with rice, tomatoes and 3/4 cup water. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: cookies
directions: Put the butter on pan and put them on the heat until the butter melts, then put the sugar and extract together.
Then put the baking powder and the vanilla extract all together, then put the eggs and then put the flour and cut in the pan.
The oven has to be heated before at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Mix together in iron pot or dutch oven.
(Do not use aluminum or plastic.)
Stir with a stick, several minutes until thick.
Let set in pot until cold.
Cut into bars.

title: fouja djedhad
directions: Brown lamb in butter; remove meat and add onion to fat.
Cook until brown.
Add flour to onion and cook until deep brown, stirring continuously.
Add onion and flour mixture to meat in 4 pint casserole.
Cover with hot water; stir in saffron, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Bake for 2 hours until the meat is tender at 325°.
Add prunes which have been soaked in cold water for 1 to 2 hours.
Continue cooking for another hour; add orange rind and sugar.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings and salt.
Stir soda into sour cream, then add alternately with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in angel cake pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a buttered casserole.
Top with the grated cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy veggie soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion soup mix.
Add V-8 and vegetables. Simmer for approximately 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Combine first five ingredients thoroughly and shape into 30 balls.
Roll balls in flour.
Brown in shortening and drain.
Pour Sweet And Sour Sauce over meat balls and simmer 15 minutes with lid on.

title: buttermilk salad(light and lively salad)
directions: Put jello and pineapple in pan and bring to a boil.
Set aside and cool.

title: old fashioned short cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a large cake pan at 350° until golden brown and knife comes out clean.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put everything except last 2 items in blender and blend.
Add oil and poppy seed; blend on low speed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: italian surprise
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with sour cream and cheese. Top with unrolled (flat) rolls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until rolls are done.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and oleo and pat firmly on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Chill.
In large bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and chocolate syrup.
Dissolve coffee in hot water.
Add to milk mixture and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into prepared pan.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional chocolate crumbs.
Return leftovers to freezer and cut and serve as desired.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pumpkin and cheese roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Grease 15 x 20-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper.
Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients all at once.
Pour into prepared pan.
Spread evenly. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen cake around edges with knife. Invert onto clean damp towel dusted with confectioners sugar. Peel off wax paper.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Place seam side down and cool.
Unroll cake.
Spread cream cheese mixture. Reroll cake.
Put in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice and serve.

title: upside-down leftover ham supper
directions: Mix ham, beans, corn, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover this and bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and spoon over the hot meat in casserole, spreading batter out evenly to seal the dish.
Return casserole to oven and bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Cut into wedges when ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Sift and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Fold in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until delicately browned.
Cookies should still be soft.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: 5 minute peach cobbler
directions: You will need a 1 1/2-quart or 9-inch square glass casserole.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg until fluffy and well blended. Sift flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt; add to mixture.
Add grated zucchini.
Blend well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: microwave cheese burger pie
directions: Combine ground beef, 1 cup instant potato flakes, 1 cup milk, egg, catsup, onion, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Spread into a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Cover with wax paper.
Heat 16 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn every 4 minutes.
Arrange 2 slices cheese on top.
Cover for 10 minutes.

title: giant cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in 2 (12-inch) pizza pans or 1 (15 x 10 x 1-inch) pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until cookies brown along edges, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package.
Drain and squeeze dry. Mix together all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In a small bowl combine soup, paprika and pepper. In a greased oblong dish arrange potatoes overlapping in a row. Sprinkle with cheese. Spoon mixture over cheese. Cover with foil, bake 400 degrees for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter a small casserole dish.
If beans are frozen, cook according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine soup and milk in casserole dish.
Add beans and either mushrooms or onions. Reserve some onions for garnish.
Top with almonds or onions. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-cheese soup
directions: Using 1/2 cauliflower and 1/2 broccoli makes a more colorful soup.

title: angel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, miniature marshmallows and sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Then chill in refrigerator until partly jelled. Whip cream cheese.
Fold in crushed pineapple (drained), pecans and whipped topping.
Put in bowl or mold and jell until set. You can serve it with some additional whipped cream on top, if you like.

title: spinach continental
directions: Arrange with drained spinach in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat milk slowly with 4 tablespoons butter and American cheese until cheese melts.
Cool, then stir in slightly beaten eggs.
Pour cheese sauce over spinach.
Saute garlic in 8 tablespoons butter until brown.
Add toasted cubes and stir until toast absorbs the butter.
Arrange over the top of spinach. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix well, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and top with your favorite icing.

title: country style beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat in chunks.
Brown meat in butter or margarine in heavy skillet, a few chunks at a time.
Place in casserole when browned.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix ingredients together in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 200° or 210°.
Stir in almonds.
Continue to stir and cook to 300°.
(Candy will change to a darker tan color.) Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits. When they are melted, spread with a spatula.
May sprinkle with ground pecans, too.
A candy thermometer is very helpful.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix the dry ingredients; sprinkle over the raisins and nuts.
Combine the mixtures, adding milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: enchiladas "beef or chicken"
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2 dish, sprayed.

title: attebery cream pie(this is my grandmother attebery's recipe)
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and cold milk. Pouring scalded milk, stir constantly until thick. Remove from heat, then pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 300° until done. Serve with whipped topping on top or Cool Whip if you like.

title: stickies
directions: Make dough of biscuit mix and 1/2 cup milk.
Roll or pat out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dot or brush dough with 1/4 stick margarine.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon over surface.
Roll up dough as for jelly roll.

title: pineapple raisin drop cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add the shortening, egg, brown sugar and pineapple. Beat all together until smooth.
Stir in the raisins and chopped nuts.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a medium mixing bowl with electric beaters, lightly beat eggs.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed to combine.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and salt.
Add to sugar mixture. Beat until smooth.
By hand, stir in nuts and orange slices. Spread batter in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Remove pan to wire cooking rack.
Cool completely.
Cut into 30 bar cookies.
Roll each cookie in powdered sugar to coat.
Store covered in powdered sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except crackers. Top with buttered crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pasta with eggplant
directions: Cook pasta.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil and saute eggplant until lightly browned.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, add 2 more tablespoons oil and saute onion for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook 3 minutes. Return eggplant to skillet with tomato sauce, heavy cream and thyme; simmer for 5 minutes.
Toss pasta shells with eggplant mixture and serve while hot.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups. Serve with raw veggies, crackers or round rye bread.

title: holiday pickles
directions: Drain jar of pickles.
Slice in strips.
Place in jar and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Shake jar every time you go past.
Eat and enjoy.

title: sausage spinach bread
directions: Allow dough to thaw.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well.
Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Beat egg.
Add about half of it to the drained spinach and reserve the rest to brush over the top of the bread.
Working with one loaf of bread at a time, roll the bread into a rectangle, 9 x 13-inches. Spread half of the spinach, sausage and Mozzarella cheese over the dough.
Sprinkle with half of the Parmesan cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style; seal all edges tightly so that filling remains inside. Lightly score tops.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Serve hot.
Repeat with other loaf.

title: golden raisins buns
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add flour, all at once.
Then, over low heat, beat with wooden spoon about 1 minute or until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth, thick dough.
Remove from heat.
Continue beating for 2 minutes to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until mixture has satin sheen.
Stir in raisins.
Drop heaping measuring tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 30
or 35 minutes; cool slightly.
Makes 20.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind together the zucchini, onion and green pepper.
Add 3 tablespoons salt.
Cover with cold water and let stand overnight. Then pour off the liquid and rinse with cold water.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil and cook 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: barbecue chicken in sack
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients (except chicken); need not cook. Place pieces of the fryer on waxed paper; salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Place in an oven cooking bag. Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Close sack tightly. (Place sack in pan in case of breaking.)
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes and cook.
Cool. Combine other ingredients with potatoes. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours to blend flavors.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: beets in orange juice
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt (if desired).
Stir in orange juice.
Arrange beets in a 1-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over beets and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion; saute until clear.
Add thawed broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Add soup; stir and simmer about 6 to 8 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Simmer a few minutes.
If too thick, add small amounts of hot water.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and pour into small baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Can make ahead and freeze until needed.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake as per instructions on package and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour this mixture evenly over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cake.
Refrigerate unused portions.

title: sally's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done by forking.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Put in bowl.
Add to macaroni the diced onions and lots of diced sweet pickles.
Drain kidney beans and run cold water over them.
Mix in with rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Hellmann's mayonnaise to all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: frosting for red velvet cakes and others
directions: Cook flour and milk over low heat until thick, stirring constantly; cool. Cream sugar, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Add cooled whip mixture. Mix until well blended.
Should be similar to whipping cream. You may use Crisco instead of margarine. It will not change the taste.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and combine with buttermilk.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes, then increase temperature to 300° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: easy cheesy hot dog casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Then remove from heat; stir in noodles and peanuts.
Mix good, then quickly put teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let them cool and become firm.
(Makes 4 dozen.)

title: eggplant and noodle casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and drain for 30 minutes.
Dry and brush with olive oil.
Broil in oven about 4 to 5 minutes per side until light brown.
Cook noodles; drain and add Ricotta or sour cream.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with broiled eggplant and sauteed onion. Sprinkle with Cavender's.
Add cooked sausage and spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Uncover and place Mozzarella on top.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes more until melted.

title: clam chowder
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes the butter and flour.
Cook together until potatoes are tender the clams, sherry, black pepper, salt, thyme, bay leaves, Tabasco, potatoes, celery, onion, green pepper and leeks.
Add baked roux (flour and butter) to cooked vegetables; stir well.
Add the half and half; simmer until hot, stirring occasionally.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Prepare before roast.
Mix flour and salt.
Make a well.
Add milk and eggs.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
After removing roast from pan, increase oven heat to 450°.
Put drippings in pan, then in oven.
Heat until it sizzles.
Pour in batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown and fluffy.
Cut into squares and serve with gravy.

title: six in one
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Spoon into casserole.
Layer rice, potatoes, onion, green pepper and tomatoes over ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: edible clay
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add confectioners sugar; knead until smooth.
Make objects on top of cupcakes or graham crackers.

title: apple dip
directions: May be used for pears, too.

title: almond bark
directions: *One (12 ounce) package semi-sweet chocolate morsels may be substituted for 3/4 pound chocolate.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix and mousse according to package directions.
Defrost Cool Whip. Crush candy bars and crumble brownies. In deep glass bowl, layer brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and candy.	Last layer should be crushed candy. Serves 10 to 14.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour sliced peaches into a deep baking dish.
Pour mixture of milk, sugar and flour over top of peaches.
Put margarine on top. Bake at 450° until top is brown, about 40 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix the cabbage, carrots and onion and set aside. Mix the dressing ingredients and pour over the cabbage.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, zucchini and oil.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; stir until well blended.
Stir in nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: wiggle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles until tender.
Layer hamburger, noodles, peas, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Put sliced cheese on top or crumble bacon on top.

title: batter-dipped hot dogs
directions: Sift together corn meal and pepper.
Add
egg, milk and shortening.
Beat	with
rotary
beater
until
smooth.
Dip wieners into batter; drain.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on
paper towels.
Makes 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: glazed graham crackers
directions: Boil sugar/butter for 2 minutes on medium-high. Break crackers and place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Place nuts on top of crackers. Pour hot liquid over top of crackers. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Immediately use spatula and remove crackers to wax paper. Cool.

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine beef, eggs, onion, oats, milk, 4 tablespoons ketchup, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and basil.
Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours until cooked through.
Top with remaining ketchup and cheese.
Melt cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: church window candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in large saucepan; cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows; stir well.
Shape into 4 large logs.
Sprinkle coconut onto waxed paper.
Roll logs in coconut until well coated. Chill overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Grease with butter.
Layer a single layer of saltine crackers on foil. Boil sugar and butter 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven. Add chips. Spread to frost.
Refrigerate and break into pieces.

title: microwave scalloped corn with ham
directions: Soap was made in the 18th century by using lye made by leaching water through ashes in an ash hopper and any fats or greases which were not used for other purposes, such as candles, cooking, etc.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar and water until it forms a hard ball in cold water. Place marshmallow cream in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup, stirring until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla. Drop from teaspoon on wax paper or buttered dish.

title: apple crunch
directions: Grease 9-inch baking pan with butter and set aside. Toss apples and lemon juice. Add to the apples the granulated sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and toss together. Turn into prepared baking dish and level mixture without marking apple slices. Combine and mix together the bread crumbs, flour, brown sugar, pecans and cubed butter until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until topping is golden brown. Serve warm sprinkled with cinnamon. Makes 9 servings.

title: venison kabobs
directions: Chop and smash garlic.
Combine lemon juice, olive oil, crushed oregano and garlic in a large, heavy-duty plastic bag. Cut venison into 2-inch chunks and place in bag, closing the bag with wire tie.
Shake well and marinate for 4 to 6 hours, turning the bag every hour.
Peel and quarter onions, cut bell pepper into 1 1/2-inch squares and cut bacon in 1 1/2-inch pieces. Prepare a charcoal fire.
Alternate chunks of venison, bacon, onion and bell pepper on skewers.
(Place bacon on both sides of venison on skewers.)
Turn skewers slowly until done.

title: slow pot potatoes
directions: Line your slow pot with aluminum foil and leave enough to cover potatoes, before cooking.
Put half of bacon, onions, potatoes and cheese in layers in slow cooker.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Again, put salt and pepper and dot with margarine.
Cover with foil.
Place cover on slow pot.
Cook on low overnight (10 to 12 hours) or cook on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer in a small casserole bowl as listed.
Heat in moderate oven until cheese is melted.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Combine everything and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into thin strips. In medium skillet, heat half of the oil. Add beef in 2 batches and stir fry until browned. Set beef aside. Reduce heat to medium. Add remaining oil. Add peppers, onion, and garlic powder and stir fry until tender crisp. Drain Fat. Add gravy and worcestershire. Heat to aboil. Return beef to pan. reduce heat to low and heat thoroughly. Serve over rice.

title: dirt cake
directions: In blender or food processor, crumb cookies, trying not to make them too fine.
Mix pudding and milk.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Blend the two mixes together and add Cool Whip.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all together and bake in large casserole dish for 1 hour at 300°.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Drain syrup from fruit.
Sift white sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Beat egg and add with fruit to dry ingredients.
Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put broken nut meats and brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: doughnuts muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In another bowl, beat egg with milk, 1/3 cup magarine and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and stir just to moisten.
Equally spoon half the batter into 12 buttered muffin cups.
Add 1/2 teaspoon jam or jelly to each.
Top equally with remaining batter. Bake in a 400° oven until deep golden (18 to 20 minutes).
Do not overbake.

title: banana split delight
directions: Crush large box of vanilla wafers; cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch oblong casserole or pan.
Mix together the powdered sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla; beat mixture at least 5 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Split 5 or 6 bananas lengthwise and dip in juice drained from pineapple.
Place dipped bananas over second layer.
Pour or spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions, or use Cool Whip and spread over mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken.
Place chicken into a baking dish. Mix chopped up broccoli, soup, cheese and milk in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend next 3 ingredients.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill.

title: mexican fiesta soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add taco seasoning, chili powder and salsa.
Add tomato soup with water (according to directions on can).
Add bean and bacon soup (no water).
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: german apple bundt cake
directions: Beat together sugar, orange juice, oil, vanilla and eggs with electric mixer at high speed. Sift together dry ingredients, then blend into first mixture. Fold in nuts. Place 1/3 of the batter in a greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle with half of a mixture of the apples, sugar and cinnamon. Pour on another 1/3 of the batter. Sprinkle on the rest of the filling and top with the last 1/3 of the batter. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool pan 10 minutes upside down, then remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: salmon divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Snip corner off pouch and drain butter sauce into saucepan. Add soup, milk, Swiss cheese and lemon juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth. Drain and flake salmon. Arrange broccoli in 2-quart oblong baking dish. Place salmon over broccoli. Arrange mushrooms on salmon; top with sauce. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease Pyrex dish with margarine.
Place frozen rolls in Pyrex dish (I usually use all 24 rolls in package).
Sprinkle pudding and pie filling over rolls, then sprinkle brown sugar over rolls. Next, add the margarine.
Use as many pecans as you like.
Place rolls in cold oven night before.
Next morning, turn oven to 350° and immediately (oven does not need to preheat) time for 20 minutes.
Turn rolls onto platter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together except nuts.
Put 1 cup of nuts in each pie shell (uncooked) and pour mixture over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: butterhorns
directions: Place yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon
sugar to activate yeast.
Let set about 10 minutes.
Scald milk.
Stir Crisco, sugar and salt into hot milk.
Let cool slightly.
Add yeast, flour and eggs.
Knead dough, place in oiled bowl (turn to coat), cover and let rise until doubled in size.

title: broccoli ring
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water with garlic until tender. Remove garlic; drain.
Melt butter; add flour and gradually pour in the cream.
Cook until thick; add beaten egg yolks and broccoli.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Season.
Pour into buttered and floured ring.
Place in pan of boiling water and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies fine.
Mix with melted margarine and sprinkle 1/2 in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and pour into
unbaked
pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 25 or 30 minutes at 300°.

title: baked venison steak
directions: Cut meat in thin strips. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Roll in flour. Brown in oil. Saute onions. Place meat and onions in small roaster. Mix onion soup with 1 1/2 cups water. Pour over meat. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. Mix 2 tablespoons flour with sour cream and small amount of water. Add to meat and simmer, but do not boil for 10 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: strawberry-spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves and pat dry.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, strawberries and almonds in bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together; pepper to taste.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and eggs.
Add fruit cocktail and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut cooked chicken into thin strips.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken and coat chicken with paprika.
Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken in oil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add onions, garlic and green pepper and saute for 3 minutes.
Add one can chicken broth and liquid from Ro-Tel tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Then add rice and stir really good; also add the Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Sprinkle the package of Monterey Jack cheese on top and cover to steam for about 5 or 10 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Add egg, flour, sugar and vinegar to pineapple juice and cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Add apples, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until served.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade and Cool Whip.
Fold in condensed milk; mix well. Tint light green.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Blend the next 3 ingredients together, then stir in onion, celery and olives.
Mix this mixture with the first mixture carefully.
Chill and serve in 1 large bowl or individually in lettuce cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and the spaghetti sauce mix; simmer for 40 minutes.
Add browned ground beef.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Layer in pan with noodles, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning.
Let cool for 1 hour and add all remaining ingredients except the Doritos.
Just before serving add Doritos.

title: good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pineapple together well, then add pineapple with juice.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts in flour; brown in olive oil.
Pour spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top, adding a slice of cheese on each piece.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: raspberry wine vinegar
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture through a wire mesh strainer, discarding pulp.
Pour into decorative bottles.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 5 cups with 13 calories per tablespoon and 0% fat.

title: fruit cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Store in refrigerator until set.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, water, butter, peanut butter and half of the cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and chocolate pieces.
Spread dough in greased and floured pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: yam cups(a holiday favorite served in a new way.)
directions: Boil yams.
When tender, remove the skin and mash the meat with the brown sugar, margarine and salt.
On a baking sheet, arrange twelve foil baking cups with liners, placing a marshmallow in each cup.
Spoon yam meat over marshmallow, sprinkling with cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Yams may be refrigerated at this point until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: burritos
directions: Cook hamburger and garlic together until done.
Drain off grease.
Heat tortilla shells; add hamburger and cheese.
Roll together.
Add tomato chunks and hot sauce as desired.

title: cheese tidbits
directions: Form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer; add egg and beat well. After sifting together dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture with a fork, then by hand, divide dough in half.
Press half into a 13 x 9-inch pan, forming 1/8-inch edge.
Fill with pie filling. Form second half of dough into a ball, then grate on large side of grater over filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be cut into squares when cooled or cut from dish and served as cobbler.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg and milk, mixing well.
Add to first mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add nuts, raisins and shortening.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cranberries.
Bring to a boil. Add cranberries and bring to a boil again.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature until jellied.
(Buy extra cranberries and put in freezer.)

title: baked eggs with ham and cheese
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese and ham in greased baking pan making 4 nests.
Break 1 egg into each nest.
Pour 1 tablespoon cream over each egg.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over each egg.
Dot with butter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in preheated oven (400°) until cheese melts and eggs set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
After removing pan from oven, let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: calzones
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Divide each loaf into 5 parts each.
One at a time, roll each dough piece on a floured board or stretch with your hands, making 10 (7-inch) squares.
Fold each dough square over half a cheese slice to form a turnover and pinch edges to seal.
(You can also ladle 1/3 cup sauce onto center of each square before making turnover, but the sauce tends to leak out.)
Heat sauce in a medium pan 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.
Place calzones about 2 inches apart on a baking sheet sprayed with no-stick spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes. Turnovers will be golden brown when done.
Ladle sauce on top of turnovers.
Makes 10 servings.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Blend together.
Good for Strawberries, Grapes, bananas etc.

title: pineapple delight-noodle kugel
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil noodles; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°, or until browned.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend
together
shortening, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Sift and
add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well to form dough.
Roll
dough
into
balls
the size of a large marble. Roll
balls
into
the combined cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 400° on a ungreased cookie sheet, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate chambord espresso torte
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Butter and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Melt the chocolate in a double boiler; add butter.
Allow butter to melt, stirring occasionally until combined.
Stir instant Espresso into Chambord in a bowl.
Whisk together eggs and sugars until liquid.
Place bowl over a pan of boiling water and whisk mixture until warm to the touch.
Immediately begin to machine whisk on high speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Volume should triple.
In a clean bowl, fold together the chocolate mixture, Chambord and almonds.
Add the egg mixture and fold quickly until color is uniform.

title: peanut butter dips
directions: Mix sugar, Rice Krispies, peanut butter and margarine in large bowl, with hands.
Roll into 1-inch balls and set on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and 1/2 of wax.
If too thick, add more wax.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate with fork and set on wax paper.
Refrigerate to speed hardening of chocolate.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: In 2-cup glass measure place butter and chocolate and cook on High (maximum power) 1 1/2 minutes or until butter is melted. Chocolate will not appear melted until stirred.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl until light and foamy.
Stir in chocolate mixture, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into 9-inch micro-proof baking dish.
Cook on High (maximum power) 6 minutes.
Brownies will still be moist but will firm as cooled.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies(5 dozen)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream together the Crisco, peanut butter, brown sugar, white sugar, unbeaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Roll balls in white granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° about 8 minutes.

title: cow patties
directions: Mix together in a medium pan the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Then add the last 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Then drop by a spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine celery, onion, salt and flour.
Add to bacon grease and cook over low heat until tender.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the potatoes in a 3-quart baking dish.
Crumble bacon on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pita bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl dissolve the sugar in the warm water and sprinkle in the dried yeast.
Leave to stand in warm place for about 10 minutes until frothy; add two cups of flour, shortening and salt.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 a minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix with a spoon.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer.
Beat for several minutes.
Bake in greased tube pan in 340° oven for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: watergate pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix together instant pudding and crushed pineapple (juice and all); stir in until well blended and then add Cool Whip.
Stir it well, then add the miniature marshmallows. Stir it well.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add pumpkin and mix. Add all dry ingredients and beat well. Stir in nuts. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine mixed vegetables and potatoes with 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Add meat and place this mixture in pie crust.
Top with other pie crust and bake at 425° about 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Sift a little flour over raisins and nuts.
Combine rest of flour with other dry ingredients.
Add oil, buttermilk, eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marie's sweet pickle
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in churn.

In enough water to cover cucumbers, add salt in a quantity sufficient to float a fresh egg; pour over cucumbers and place something heavy enough to hold cucumbers under brine water; let stand for 14 days.
Remove cucumbers and wash and slice them.
Discard brine water and return cucumbers to churn.
In enough water to cover cucumbers, mix in alum, pour over cucumbers, cover and let sit for 24 hours.
Remove cucumbers and wash them.
Discard alum water and return cucumbers to churn.
Add vinegar to cucumbers and let stand for 6 hours. Remove cucumbers and layer them with sugar in churn, after discarding vinegar.
Let stand until ready to place in jars.
There is no heating or cooking necessary and pickles can be kept in churn, if you desire.

title: french almond meringues
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cool 5 minutes.
Combine egg whites and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar, almonds and cooled chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen!

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into mold.
Freeze.
Leave at room temperature for one hour before serving.

title: mama's texas breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Add potatoes, pepper and onion. Cook slowly, 15 to 20 minutes or until sausage and potatoes are done.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Add to sausage mixture and cook until eggs are thickened.
Stir as needed.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour into lightly greased angel food pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breast with rice
directions: Combine chicken soup and water in large casserole dish.
Add chicken and sprinkle rice and onion soup mix over chicken.
Top with mushroom soup.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Do not open oven while baking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour 1 cup of pineapple juice in a large, glass bowl and add instant pudding.
Stir until thick.
Add fruit and serve.

title: frozen party salad
directions: Add salad dressing to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in fruit, sugar and food coloring.
Fold in marshmallows, then whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and freeze.
Unmold and surround with lettuce.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in slow oven, 300° to 325°, until done, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix squash, sugar, oil and eggs. Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with squash mixture.
Bake in 2 pans at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Cut apples in eighths and arrange in 9-inch crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
In order not to overbake crust edge, cover with strip of aluminum foil; remove last 10 minutes.

title: very easy pie crust
directions: Mix all together.
Divide into two balls.
Use two pieces of wax paper, putting one ball in middle, after sprinkling paper with flour.
Roll with rolling pin to size desired.
Can be used for two (1 crust) pies or 1 (2 crust) pie.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine in saucepan over low heat. Stir occasionally until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn.
Toss until fully covered. With hands slightly moistened with cold water, form into balls. Decorate with fruit, nuts or candy, if desired.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: On waxed paper, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream margarine, sugar and orange rind.
Add flour mixture in 4 additions, alternating with orange juice, beating only until smooth.
Beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks and fold into other mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch or 12-inch tube pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out on a wire rack to cool.

title: puffy cheese omelet
directions: In largest mixer bowl, beat egg whites at high speed of mixer until soft peaks form.
Then in smaller bowl, using same beaters, beat yolks, mayonnaise and water.
Gently pour yolk mixture over beaten whites.
Fold together carefully.
In 9-inch pie plate, place butter.
Microwave at High 1 minute, swirl to coat dish. Pour egg mixture into pie plate.
Microwave at Medium 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish after 3 minutes until set but still glossy on top.
Sprinkle cheese over omelet, microwave at Medium 1/2 to 1 minute.
Fold 1/2 omelet over the other 1/2.
Gently slide onto serving dish.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: old fashion corn bread
directions: Mix salt, meal and water in medium mixing bowl; grease 9-inch skillet.
Pour mix into skillet; bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken; set aside.
Prepare pineapple, green onions, green pepper and water chestnuts and set aside.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch; stir in vinegar, pineapple juice, soy sauce, pepper sauce, and salt. Then set aside.
Saute chicken in small amount of oil in skillet until done.
Add sauce and cook until sauce boils and is clear.
Add pineapple mixture and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring until heated through.
Serve with steamed rice. Serves 3.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Make at least 4 hours ahead.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine sugar and syrup. Microwave at High 3 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes until peanuts are light brown, stirring every 2 minutes. Add butter and vanilla; stir well.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet; let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: conch salad
directions: Wash conch.
Dice into small pieces.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Dice tomatoes.
Mix conch, onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Pour Old Sour or lime juice over the mixture.
Let sit in refrigerator for an hour or so.

title: crunchy sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix flour, coconut, brown sugar and nuts; set aside.
Melt butter in milk.
Add to sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with mixture that was set aside.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sand sculpture
directions: You will also need a spoon and a saucepan.

title: wassail(great holiday drink)
directions: Press cloves into orange.
Place in heavy large saucepan.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine in large bowl all the remaining ingredients.
Add to apple mixture.
Mix all together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pear jello
directions: Drain pears and heat them in a saucepan.
Pour in jello and dissolve.
When jello is thoroughly dissolved and mixture is heated, blend together with the rest of ingredients in a blender. Pour into a jello mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: *peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add peanuts; stir constantly.
Cook slowly until mixture reaches 293° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add baking soda.
Beat rapidly and spread as thin as possible on buttered cookie sheets.
When cool enough so that you can work with it (about 5 minutes), pull to stretch and make it even thinner.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add eggs 1 at a time.
Mix well; stir in 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.
Add sour cream, then add one flavor or all three, 1 teaspoon each.
Mix 1 cup of flour at a time.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake.
Mix Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake while warm.
Frost with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: mock coconut cream pie(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Using the back of a spoon, spread squash over bottom and up sides of plate; set aside.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Have water come to a boil.
Put salt in water.
This prevents eggs going into your water if shell is cracked.
Put lid over pot with eggs.
Cut stove to low heat.
Let eggs cook for 10 minutes. Eggs will be ready for deviling.
Shell eggs.
Mash yellow and add the following:
mayonnaise, mustard and Texas Pete.
Add vinegar and salt.
Garnish with green olive and paprika.

title: chutney sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in baking pan.
Dab with butter and sprinkle 1/4 cup crushed crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Melt butter in a bowl.
Mix 2 sugars together.
Roll out each biscuit into a pencil log.
Tie then gently into a knot.
Dip them in butter and roll them in the sugar coating them.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
After they have cooled, can reheat in microwave. They're great!

title: fix and forget pork chops and rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, undrained corn, carrots, onion and thyme; bring to a boil.
Stir in soup. Transfer to a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Trim fat from chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on rice mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Stir together bread crumbs and paprika.
Add oleo; toss gently to mix.
Remove foil from chops; sprinkle bread crumb mixture over chops.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes longer or until chops are done and rice is tender.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or in microwave 12 to 14 minutes or until heated through.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add eggs, onion, cheese, and muffin mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese cloud
directions: Trim bread.
Spray pan with Pam.
Arrange 6 slices in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with cheese, then sausage.
Cover with other 6 slices of bread.
Beat remaining ingredients well and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lasting friendship
directions: Take love, understanding and comfort and mix well with forgiveness and caring. Sprinkle in some generosity and add a dash of praise. Cover with trust and bake in sunshine.
This recipe serves all.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.

title: garden zucchini pie
directions: If using whole potatoes, wash and peel.
In a food processor, fitted with a medium shredding disc, coarsely shred the potatoes. Or you can shred potato with a grater.
To prevent darkening, place shredded potatoes in a bowl of cold water immediately after shredding.
Rinse potato shreds well and drain.
Squeeze potato shreds to remove any excess water.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into oblong pan or dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, peanut butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture on low speed until just blended.
Form dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Press chocolate kiss into center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 3 minutes.

title: potato spice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Delicious sprinkled over baked potatoes, fries, etc.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening (butter or margarine or Crisco) and sugar. Add egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well. Let set covered in refrigerator until it feels thick enough to handle for rolled cookies.
Roll out and cut with large, round cutter.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned (about 10 minutes).

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well (do not peel); halve and quarter potatoes to make wedges.
Place on cookie sheet.
Separate potatoes on sheet, skin side down.
Melt margarine; pour over potatoes, making sure all are coated.
Sprinkle well with seasoned salt, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Cook in a 400° oven until potatoes are done.

title: spicy beef with peppers
directions: In medium bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons sherry, garlic and red pepper until smooth.
Add beef; toss to coat well.
In small bowl, stir in remaining cornstarch, soy sauce, dry sherry and water until smooth; set aside.
In wok or large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over medium heat.
Add pepper; stir-fry 1 minute and remove.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons of oil; add beef and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Add pepper; restir cornstarch mix and add to wok.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil; let simmer until it is done.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and beat until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Form dough (a teaspoon at a time) into balls.
Roll half of each ball in cinnamon/sugar.
Place balls, unsugared side down, on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast until very tender.
Break into pieces.
Add to pan drippings the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Add water, salt and pepper to vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make a white sauce with margarine, flour and half and half.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add undrained vegetables.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: no bake chocolate haystacks
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In saucepan, combine last 4 ingredients, stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over oat mixture.
Drop in small clumps onto waxed paper.
Let cool and store.

title: turkey-cheddar noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; cook broccoli tender-crisp.
Drain and coarsely chop.
Make white sauce of milk, flour and oleo.
Stir seasoning into white sauce; stir cheese into white sauce.
In 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch casserole, buttered, place 1/2 noodles; cover with turkey and 2/3 amount of broccoli.
Pour half of cheese sauce over noodles and turkey.
Cover with remaining noodles; press remaining broccoli flowerets into noodles.
Pour over remaining cheese sauce; sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party trash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "dirt"
directions: Let butter and cream cheese soften.
Mix butter, cream cheese and vanilla in a separate bowl.
Mix instant pudding (follow box directions) and add sugar.
Combine both mixtures and fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies and layer with mixture.
Blend some Oreo cookies (about 8) and layer on top for dirt look.
Add gummy worms and fake flowers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, rice, onion and celery.
Mix soups and Cheez Whiz; pour over broccoli.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish the green beans and the soup. Top with Funyuns.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: apricot balls
directions: Combine apricots, coconut and nuts in a large mixing bowl; add condensed milk, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll each in powdered sugar.
Yield:
About 9 dozen.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix soup with hamburger.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake until Tots are done, around 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Mix. Sift together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with coffee. Add thinly sliced apples and raisins. Set in oven preheated to 375° for 15 minutes. Then turn to 350° and bake 1 hour. Bake in loaf pan.

title: mexican style casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together; drain.
Add taco mix and Ro-Tel tomatoes; simmer.
Cook rice as directed on package. Layer rice, meat, rice and meat.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Season	round
steak
with
salt
and pepper.
Cut into serving
pieces and place in crock-pot with sliced onion which has been separated into rings.
Add potatoes, green beans and garlic. Top
with	soup
and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on Low for 8
to 10	hours
or
High for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove cover during last half hour if too much liquid has collected.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put eggs and red beets in container.
Add more sugar and vinegar, if needed.
Make sure eggs are covered with juice. Cover with lid.

title: blueberry pie(2 pies)
directions: Sprinkle pie shells with chopped nuts and bake.
Cool before adding filling.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together. Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Add to cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in cooled pie shell and top with blueberries and chill.

title: kottsoppa(meat soup)
directions: Place the meat in a large kettle and add the water.
Bring to a boil.
Skim off any scum.
Add the salt and reduce the heat. Simmer about 2 hours.
Add the carrots, turnip, celery, onion and scallions.
Sprinkle with the pepper and bring to a boil again. Reduce the heat and simmer another hour.
Remove the meat; cut into pieces and return to the soup.
Remove the cloves.
Serve piping hot.

title: melt in your mouth bundt cake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed to a large mixer bowl.
Blend 30 seconds on lowest speed. Scrape sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides.
Grease a Bundt pan well.
Pour batter and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: mocha-almond biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread almonds on baking sheet and bake 12 to 14 minutes until lightly toasted.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Whisk eggs, egg whites and vanilla and add to dry ingredients; mix until smooth.

title: the best pie crust(never fails)
directions: Mix flour and lard (usual method, I use my fingers rather than knives).
Beat egg, vinegar and milk and add to flour and lard mixture.
It rolls out perfect.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together; add enough fruit juice to achieve desired consistency.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Line cookie sheets with foil.

title: cabbage and bean salad
directions: Grate cabbage in a medium bowl.
Add beans including sauce. Combine mayonnaise and vinegar; add to cabbage and beans.
Mix well.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss well.
Serve on salad plates. Serves 6 to 8.

title: helmut's frikadeller
directions: Combine meat, chopped onions, eggs, breadcrumbs and spices. Shape into Frikadeller (burgers) and fry in pan until pretty dark. Should be crusty on outside and well done on the inside.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 14 to 20 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: angel cookies
directions: Measure and sift together the flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Beat together until fluffy the butter, shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Gradually add in dry ingredients.
Blend in walnuts.
Form dough into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Dip in water, then in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes on cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole bowl; add 1 cup rice.
Add chicken. Add Lipton soup mix and water; add chicken soup and water.
Add Veg-All next.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be stored before serving.
Can serve as a meat dish. Very good.

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Boil salted water. Add potatoes. Cook about 15 minutes. Drain. Cover with milk. Add butter, salt and pepper. Simmer. Pair up with toasted cheese sandwiches for a great meal on the day of the first snow of the year.

title: fork cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg; add vanilla and blend well.
Add dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture. Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork dipped in sugar.
You can top with a half pecan or cherry if you wish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chinese hot and sour soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg and green onions. Bring to the boil over high heat until slightly thickened. Gradually pour in the egg, stirring constantly in one direction. Remove from heat; stir in green onions. Garnish with additional onions as desired. Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple-pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into serving dish and garnish with celery leaves and orange slices.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well,
pour
into
greased
13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake for 1 hour on 350°.

title: marinated olives
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Toss. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: rice primavera
directions: Heat garlic with oil in large skillet over medium-high heat; discard garlic.
Cook broccoli, zucchini and mushrooms in oil until almost tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes and parsley; cook one minute longer.
Remove vegetables; set aside.
Place mayonnaise in same skillet; stir in milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Add rice; toss to coat.
Stir in reserved vegetables; heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Measure
dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add soup and shortening.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and water; beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 8 or 9-inch pans, 1 hour for tube pan.
Can add raisins or nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 4 oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a
greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before slicing.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy in double boiler.
Pour into Cool Whip.
Mix well. Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: pineapple pie
