directions: Drain pineapple.
Put in bowl.
Add sour cream and pudding mixes.
Stir together until all mixed.
Pour into crust and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pudding cake
directions: Cream white sugar and butter.
Add milk; blend well.
Add flour, cinnamon and soda; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter in greased cake pan (9 to 10-inch square).

title: chinese pie in crock-pot
directions: Brown ground beef with diced peppers and onion. Drain well. Place ground beef mixture in crock-pot; sprinkle gravy mix over ground beef mixture. Toss diced potatoes with melted butter to coat and add to crock-pot; add whole kernel corn and creamed corn. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours. Taste and adjust seasonings. Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave milk and chocolate on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered square dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar in saucepan, mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cook 15 minutes longer.
Put into hot sterilized jar and seal.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in small casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand milk and milk until blended.
Add pudding and beat until creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, bananas and wafers in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: col. sanders' waffles
directions: Sift the dry ingredients with the flour.
Mix in shortening as for pie crust.
Add the buttermilk and unbeaten eggs.
Bake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Any of the cream soups are good, celery, broccoli, asparagus.

title: beef bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Divide into 3 parts and roll into 6-inch rolls. Wrap in Handi-wrap.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Unwrap and put in broiler pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Refrigerate or put in freezer.

title: shrimp potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Put to boil in water with 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cook until tender, but not mushy.
In a separate pot, melt margarine and add shrimp.
Saute for 10 minutes; add green onions and cook for 5 minutes more.
Add mushroom soup and heat until bubbly. Lower heat and add cheese, cut up in chunks.
Put one layer of potatoes in dish and 1/2 of the shrimp mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake until heated through at 350 degrees.
Serves 6.

title: white bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Cover beans with water.
Add onions and celery.
Bring to boil.
Add ham, tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook slowly about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add water as needed. Great with cornbread.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Split rolls open; peel lid aside.
On bottom, place chopped ham and Swiss cheese.
Replace lid.
Top with dressing.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first four ingredients and form into small acorn sized balls.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil noodles until soft.
Add sauce to meat and heat.
Layer noodles and sauce in pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in 450° oven.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: country chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Meanwhile, on a piece of waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken into butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Place skin-side up in ungreased baking dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Add wine, onion and parsley to remaining melted butter (about 1/2 cup).
When chicken is golden, pour sauce all over.
Bake 3 to 5 more minutes.

title: spanish corn
directions: Drain corn.
Heat oil.
Add corn and pepper and saute for 3 minutes in heavy 10 or 12-inch skillet.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients and cook in covered skillet over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven. Combine the whole kernel corn, cream-style corn, sour cream, melted butter, eggs and muffin mix.
Mix well and pour into Dutch oven. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until done. Should be firm to the touch. Top with Cheddar cheese and let it melt.

title: pork chop-potato-onion skillet
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In a large heavy skillet over medium heat render the fat.
Add chops.
Turn once and brown well. Layer onion, then potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and add more water if needed.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve from skillet.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place oleo, peanut butter and vanilla in square 10 x 10-inch size microwave dish.
Heat on High for 3 minutes.
Mix in 4 cups of powdered sugar; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes. Cut.
Doesn't have to be refrigerated to keep.

title: glycerin soap bubbles
directions: Mix together and allow to cool.
Put mixture into a small baby food jar.

title: coconut pie
directions: Makes its own crust.
Mix in order given.
Pour into 10-inch greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a large saucepan (3-quart size).
Add milk gradually; mix thoroughly.
Bring to a "bubbly" boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool and beat until it thickens and loses gloss.
Quickly pour and spread in buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine melted margarine with sugar and milk in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir constantly until boiling rapidly.
Stir at a rapid boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat well with spoon. Spread on large greased sheet and cool before cutting.
Timing is important!

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, then add pecans.
Chill in long roll, then slice thin.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal and blend well. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Melt bits together over hot water (not boiling).
Blend and spread over mixture.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: hamantashen cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets. Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat together. Add more juice or flour, depending on the consistency of dough. Roll dough into a ball. Divide into 4 parts. On a floured board roll out each section to about 1/8 inch thick. Using a round biscuit or cookie cutter, cut 3 inch circles. Place 1/2 to 2/3 tsp. of filling in the center of each circle. To shape into triangle, bring up right and left sides to meet at the center above filling. Bring top flap down to the center and pinch edges tightly together. Place on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart. Bake 20 minutes.

title: southern stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers and remove seeds and cook 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Cook chicken livers, bacon, onion, celery and garlic until tender.
Add mushrooms, rice and seasonings.
Stuff peppers.
Arrange in baking pan; seal and freeze.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt oleo in milk; mix with flour and pour over pie.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake according to the package (9 x 13-inch pan).
While cake is warm, poke many holes.
Pour can of milk over the cake. Pour topping sauce over the cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Spread Cool Whip evenly over caramel and top with crushed Heath bars.

title: quick and good casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in seasonings.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and rice.
Mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Replace top and simmer 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice on apples.
Combine cornstarch and sugar and sprinkle on apples. Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle crumb mixture on apples.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 30 minutes.

title: company chili
directions: Combine
ground beef, sausage and onion in a heavy pan. Cook until
beef
is browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain off
fat. Drain pinto beans, reserving liquid.
Add liquid to meat mixture, stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Add about 1/2 water if needed.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes. Add beans and cook additional 15 minutes.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Beat with mixer on high 1 1/2 minutes until smooth.
Grease pie tin.
Bake in moderate oven until knife comes out clean.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, pecans, 1/2 c. sugar and melted butter; press into a 7 by 11 inch baking pan, bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Beat cream cheese and 3/4 c. sugar till fluffy.
Fold in cool whip and spread over cooled crust.
Chill in refrigerator. Dissolve gelatin in 1 c. boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and drained pineapple.	Pour mixture over cream cheese layer and chill.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of dish.
Spread avocado (mashed) on bean dip.
Spread sour cream/taco seasoning on avocado.
Sprinkle grated cheese on sour cream. Chill the 4 layers.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: *Sprinkle remaining onions over casserole during last 5 minutes for crunchy topping.

title: pineapple molasses jumbles
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg, molasses and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and spices.
Fold in coconut and walnuts.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with reserved pineapple juice and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: k-jam's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: bishop's nightcap
directions: Stick the cloves in the orange and roast in fireplace or bake in oven.
Put small quantities of spices in a pan with water and boil.
Heat the wine, but do not boil.
Add sugar, juice and lemon.
Leave on stove for 10 minutes.
Strain and add nutmeg. Serve piping hot.

title: gauyere
directions: Combine 1 cup of water and first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Add flour all at once.

Beat over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan (does not separate, about 1 minute). Remove from heat and continue beating to cool mixture (2 minutes). Add eggs, beating after each and continue until mixture has sheen.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon into buttered pan in shape of circle.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until puffed and golden. Serve while warm.

title: costume magic makeup
directions: Mix shortening and cornstarch until creamy.
Add dishwashing detergent and mix.
Add food coloring and mix until color is even. The detergent keeps the food coloring from staining the skin and clothes.

title: quick pheasant with rice
directions: Sprinkle soup mix into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice over soup mix.
Add pheasant pieces.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over pheasant.
Cover, bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle with onion rings.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: chili cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat over medium heat, stirring often, until heated through (180°).
Remove from direct heat. Yields 1 gallon.

title: cheese bake
directions: Toss together cracker crumbs, margarine and curry powder. Grease an 11 x 16-inch pan and line with 3/4 of mixture.
Layer onion and then shredded cheese on top of crust.

title: easy spinach lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: caraway-sour cream cabbage
directions: In saucepan, bring the water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling. Add cabbage and onion.
Cook, covered, until crisp-tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.
Add enough water to cooking liquid to make 3/4 cup.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until lightly browned).
While hot, sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Let melt.
Spread and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: angel cake dessert
directions: Mix vanilla instant pudding mix with crushed pineapple and milk.
Let set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook sauce slowly.
Add hamburger or meatballs, after frying, to sauce.
Cook for 1 hour or more.
Serves 12 people.

title: pineapple cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Discard 2 tablespoons of pineapple syrup and mix remaining syrup and pineapple with melted butter and egg.
Stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Stir in pecans and cranberries.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Place egg, vinegar, seasonings and 1/4 cup of oil in blender. Blend until smooth.
With blender running, slowly add remaining oil in steady stream until smooth.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and top with flakes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Excellent for buffet with baked ham and pasta salad when entertaining a large number of people.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease 13 x9-inch baking dish. Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix
sugar
and cocoa.	Add milk and margarine.
Do not stir. Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla. Stir until
smooth.
Spread
on	waxed paper.
After cool cut into squares.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and flour and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the pineapple mixture, then cover with crushed Ritz crackers and pour melted butter or oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain grease.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chew cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Spread in thin layer in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; spread on topping.

title: hoosier potato salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together (mixture will be thick).
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with 6 to 8 slices crumbled bacon. Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.
Recipe can be doubled. Actually improves with reheating.

title: potato stuffy
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1 c. cheese and crushed cereal on top. Bake 1 hour & 15 minutes at 325°.

title: golden's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well, add eggs, one at a time; add milk, flour and salt alternately.
Grease large tube pan.
Start in cold oven and cook at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
This is a very pretty pound cake.

title: one dish meal
directions: Put salt, pepper, garlic salt and Greek seasoning in bottom of electric frying pan.
Form meat into a large patty to cover the whole bottom of the pan.
Add another layer of 4 seasonings.
Put 1/2 can of soup over meat.
Layer potatoes, onions and carrots. Add more seasoning and more soup.
Layer cabbage and mushrooms. Add remaining soup.
Let simmer until meat and vegetables are done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: every day meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Form in 2 loaves.
Cover with picante sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mac's hot chili
directions: When oil is hot in 6-quart pot, add meat, stirring constantly, until meat is gray (near brown).
Add water and cook on bubbling simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Thicken, if desired, over cornmeal and water.
If much fat, may skin.
Cook pinto beans separately and add at last. Serve over raw onions on side.

title: nutty-topped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush tomato skins with oil.
Place, cut side up, in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt; set aside.

title: sugar-free orange topping
directions: Mix together well.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: rum punch(makes about 1 gallon)
directions: If you wish, add a little sugar and/or bitters.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Junket, milk and vanilla.
Freeze.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken chasseur
directions: Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
In large skillet, brown coated chicken in oil.
Stir in seasonings and scallions.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add broth and wine.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Gently stir in mushrooms and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cut up cake into chunks.
Pour layer of cake chunks in bottom of square baking dish (about 1/2 of cake).
Beat sour cream, pudding and milk together.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on top of cake in pan.
Pour 1/2 pie filling on top of that.
Repeat layers of cake, pudding mixture and cherry pie filling.
Chill about 2 to 3 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice onion fine and put in deep Dutch oven.
Add enough oil to cover.
Put on low heat until onion is slightly brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar gradually and cream together thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough well.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place ball on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Make crisscross patterns.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Combine flour, baking soda, pumpkin spices, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well; pour mixture into 11 1/4 x 17 1/4 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.
Cut into squares; sprinkle with powdered sugar or top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise, thyme, pepper and curry powder.
Season with salt to taste.
Serve on croissant. Makes approximately 1-1/2 cups.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Beat 4 large eggs and add 3/4 cup sugar, pinch of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Add this to 2 cups scalded milk and butter the size of a walnut. Pour into a partially baked 10-inch pie crust. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Put in covered container to store in refrigerator.
Fill greased muffin cup 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° (in miniature pans, bake 10 minutes).
Makes 36 regular size muffins.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt shortening; add brown sugar to oil.
Stir well until mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
After each addition, add dry ingredients, nut meats and chocolate bits.
Mixture will be stiff. Pour into greased 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
After it has been in the oven a few minutes, shake pan so it will fall.
Remove from oven; when about cool, cut into squares.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into deep dish. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: best cinnamon rolls(so yummy on a saturday morning!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in water for about 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with beater until bubbles appear.
Add about 3 1/4 cups flour slowly.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese. Combine soup with wine or water; stir well and spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with crushed stuffing mix, the drizzle with butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If using Pyrex, bake at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine biscuit mix and seasonings in bowl.
Coat chicken pieces with dry mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender, basting frequently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into low, flat casserole dish. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: tuna wedges
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs with fork, then add rice, onions and undrained tuna.
Mix well.
Add melted butter to tuna along with crumbs and thyme.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in round casserole dish and bake for approximately 15 minutes at 300°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first three ingredients; roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; press 1 chocolate Kiss in center of each while hot.

title: rock cornish game hens
directions: Remove giblets from hens. Wipe hens with damp cloth; tie legs together with string.
Melt butter in Dutch oven over medium heat. Put hens in Dutch oven; brown well on all sides.
Remove hens; keep warm.
Place rice in Dutch oven; cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, salt, bouillon and red wine.
Place hens on top of mixture.
Cover with tightly closed lid.
Lower heat; simmer for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until rice is tender and hens are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In a large saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add corn, salt and pepper. Heat.
Stir in cheese and macaroni; heat until cheese is melted. If too thick, add 2 tablespoons milk.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan all the ingredients. Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute, stirring always. Take off flame and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Use over ice cream.

title: el dorado beef-cheese casserole
directions: Place beef in cold skillet and brown. Add onion, garlic salt and tomato sauce. Combine sour cream and cottage cheese with green chilies. Crush tortilla chips in bottom of well-buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Add half the meat mixture; cover with half the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with half the grated cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Garnish with reserved tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; let start to gel.
Add pineapple, walnuts, apples and oranges; gel until firm.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and shortening, then sift the flour, salt, cocoa and soda into the cream mixture with the water.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers or 2 loaf cakes.

title: spinach noodle bake
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with undrained spinach, noodles, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with toasted almonds, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walnut penuche
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil, letting the foil extend 2-inches above sides.
Grease lightly.

title: easy, quick chuck pot roast
directions: Trim fat from blade chuck roast.
Put into Corning Ware pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: pork-e-pine balls
directions: Mix ground beef, egg and rice.
Shape into small balls. Brown.
Add seasoning mix and water (amount on box) and simmer until done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine onions, cucumbers and salt.
Let set 1 hour.
Drain off all liquid.
Put in pan with vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and cinnamon stick.
Cook 20 minutes after comes to boil. Pack in jars and seal.
Water bath 10 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill.

title: cucumber bites
directions: Cut cucumber into 1/2-inch slices.
Hollow out about 1/2 inch. Chill.
Chop pulp, combine with remaining ingredients.
Fill with mixture.
Serve remainder as dip.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine in saucepan and boil on medium heat.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetable mixture.
Mix well and store, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 2-quarts.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
To milk, add sugar, Crisco and salt.
Cool slightly.
Add yeast, flour and soda.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll and shape as desired.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pecans) together.
Put in refrigerator for a couple hours to chill.
Make into ball and roll in nuts.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer cooked broccoli in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Place chicken pieces (cut into bite size pieces) over broccoli. Mix soups, mayonnaise and juice together and spread over top. Just before baking, top with croutons and cheese.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in warm oven just to melt, about 3 minutes.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Squeeze thawed spinach very dry and add to egg mixture, along with melted butter, chilies and cheeses.
Pour mixture into pan and bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Cut in 60 squares for hors d'oeuvres.

title: theresa's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
In a separate bowl, sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamy mixture; gradually mix in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Divide into 2 parts (for easier rolling) and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll dough approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with desired cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen large cookies.

title: nachos
directions: Spread package of cream cheese on bottom of pie plate.
Spread can of chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle the 2 cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy hamburger quiche(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Warm oven at 350°.
Brown the meat.
Drain fat.
Blend next 3 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese and onion.
Turn into the pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel chews
directions: In large bowl measure corn flakes, rice cereal, coconut and nuts.
In a double boiler, over low heat, melt the caramels and cream.
Pour caramel over cereal mixture;
combine.
With buttered hands, make small balls.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Keep covered.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Toss with crackers to coat. Takes 3 to 4 minutes to coat well.

title: peach poundcake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time and mix after each.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Mix together the sour cream and peaches.
Add the flour and sour cream alternately to the butter mixture.
Begin and end with flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Sti rin flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 75 to 80 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: In skillet, brown beef in shortening; pour off fat. Add soup, 1/2 cup water, ketchup, mustard, garlic, Tabasco sauce and seasonings. Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add onions; cook 40 minutes more. Add green pepper and mushrooms; cook 20 minutes longer or until tender. Stir now and then. Gradually blend 1/4 cup water into flour until smooth; slowly stir into stew. Cook, stirring until thickened. Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix in order given.
Form dough into small round balls and bake.
Lift the balls from the baking sheet and roll in confectioners sugar until heavily coated.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, then increase temperature to 325° and bake for 10 minutes.
Amount: 4 dozen.

title: blake's lollipop cookies
directions: You will also need 20 to 24 popsicle sticks.

title: oatmeal cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Place in an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: In double boiler, dissolve chocolate bars and marshmallows with milk and salt.
Let cool.
Whip the cream and fold into cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until set.

title: martha pippens' strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and salt.
Cook mixture, bringing to a boil.
Mixture will bubble and should be cooked until mixture thickens.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Mixture becomes clear.
When thickened, add 3 tablespoons wild strawberry jello.
Stir.
Let cool.
Cut strawberries into pie crust (may use whole berries) and then pour sauce over strawberries.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Decorate top with strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: crab delight
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium-high.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic 3 minutes.
Add remaining scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucine noodles.
Toss and heat through.

title: banana-cranberry holiday bread
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in

hot butter, cook cranberries, chopped nuts and cinnamon about 10 minutes or until cranberries pop, stirring mixture frequently. Remove skillet from heat. In large bowl, stir together orange and lemon peels and juice, mashed bananas, brown sugar, egg whites and egg. Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. In medium bowl, stir together flour, whole-wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to egg mixture. Stir until blended. Fold in cranberry mixture just until mixed. Spoon into prepared pans and bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour. Let stand for 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Makes 12 loaves.

title: mexican macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add chili powder, corn, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over drained macaroni and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Top with Pepperidge Farm Stuffing mix (1 c mixed with 2 Tbsp butter). Refrigerate over night.
Bake in 350 degree oven about 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/3 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
In skillet, brown patties (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat.
Add remaining soup, ketchup, Worcestershire and mustard.
Gradually blend water into flour until smooth.
Stir into soup mixture.
Cover, cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter.
Peel and mash the avocados.
Add some lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread on top of bean dip. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Put on top of avocados.
Place green onions on top of this mixture.
Top with tomatoes, then black olives and then Cheddar cheese.

title: marguerites
directions: Boil sugar and water until syrup will spin a long thread when dropped from the tines of a fork.
Remove from fire.
Add marshmallows, cut in pieces.
Do not stir.
Pour into stiffly beaten egg whites; beat until stiff.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pile on crackers and bake in slow oven (325° to 350°) until delicately browned.

title: easy crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Mix together in 4-quart or larger crock-pot. Cover and cook on high for 6 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients, except whipping cream.
Mix well.
Whip cream and fold in.
Freeze at least overnight.

title: lemon cake sandwich cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, adding just enough water to give mixture the consistency of cookie dough.
(Do not add over 1/4 cup.)
Spoon out onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at temperature indicated on cake mix box.
Remove from cookie sheet when done and let cool.
When cooled, ice the flat side of one cookie and place another cookie on top to make a cookie sandwich.

title: baked chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Arrange the beef on the bottom of a baking dish.
Place chicken breasts, rolled with bacon on top.
Pour soup and sour cream mixture over chicken and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes 4 servings.
May be frozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put melted margarine in 2 1/4-quart casserole dish.
Pour peaches over margarine and stir slightly. Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Add to dish by tablespoonful evenly.
Bake at 350° until brown and thick, approximately 1 hour.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish or round mold.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together cream cheese and Miracle Whip, gradually adding lemon jello.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Whip cream.
Fold into lemon mixture with marshmallows.
Spread on top of cherry jello. Top with nuts if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish until bubbly at 350°.

title: cucumber dill salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.

title: cinnamon-apple brunch bake
directions: 1) In sauce pan, melt butter, stir in brown sugar, apple pie filling, cinnamon and vanilla. Spread half of apple mixture in a 2 quart shallow baking dish.

title: flowerpot chocolate mousse
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl mix pudding and milk, then fold in Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Line a clay pot with tinfoil and put a portion of cookie mixture into bottom of pot.
Pour the mixture in the pot.
Top with crumbs.
Keep refrigerated until serving time. Put plastic or silk flowers into center of garden trowel for serving.

title: english muffins
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warmed bowl.
Sprinkle yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add additional flour to make stiff dough; knead (may be sticky).
Cover; let rise about 1 hour. Sprinkle board with cornmeal.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with round cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise for about 45 minutes.
Remove muffins and place on greased griddle (medium heat).
Bake for about 10 minutes on each side (top of stove).

title: california orange chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Arrange chicken pieces in a baking dish with lid.
Add garlic and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and black pepper.
Cover dish with lid.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: scrambled eggs, bacon and tortillas
directions: In a medium sized pan, fry tortillas in cooking oil, stirring until browned. Add crumbled bacon or diced ham (if desired) and warm.
Add eggs and scramble entire mixture over medium heat until eggs are cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: bible soup (lentil)(genesis 25:34)
directions: Combine in kettle lentils and water.
Cook 30 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer just until carrots are tender.
Check seasonings and serve.
Serves 6. Recipe can be doubled and freezes well.

title: crabmeat dish
directions: In electric frypan, melt butter at 250°, then add onions and stir until tender.
Stir in flour, bouillon granules, salt and pepper.
Pour in half and half and milk, stirring until thickened. Add rest of ingredients and heat through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: duncan hines cake mix
directions: Prepare cake batter.
You might have to adjust the eggs, oil and/or water amounts according to the directions on the package. Stir in approximately 1 cup of your favorite snack.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans.
Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Equally fill coffee cans and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Leave in cans to cool.

title: barbecue sauce(zaberers)
directions: Saute onions.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Great for thin slices of beef.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Break up bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook the sausage and spread over bread.
Add the grated cheese over the sausage. Mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over the bread, cheese and sausage layers.
Prepare the night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° until eggs are set.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: passover brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water and cool.
Beat eggs and salt until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in cooled chocolate mixture.
Gradually add cake meal and beat until well blended.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while still hot.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 3/4 teaspoon sugar in warm water. Let stand for 5 minutes. Add the milk, butter, sweet potatoes, salt and remaining sugar. Mix until smooth. Add 4 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place doubled, about 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay out crescent rolls in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Chop up all vegetables, real fine.
Add vegetables 1 layer at a time, then add bacon pieces and top with cheese.

title: hootenany cake
directions: Grease bottom of tube pan.
In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients; beat for 5 minutes.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon together.
Put 1/3 of nut mixture in bottom of tube pan.
Add 1/2 cup of cake mixture.
Add another 1/3 cup of nut mixture and the remainder of cake batter.
Add remainder of nut mixture on top of cake.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: easy eggnog
directions: In the cup, place all ingredients and mix well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and marinate for 3 hours or overnight.

title: tomatoes 'n rice
directions: Cook rice. Saute onions, bell pepper, hot pepper and garlic salt in margarine. Stir in canned tomatoes. Fold in rice. Mixture should be slightly juicy, if not, add a little water. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet 'n sour carrots (salad)
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place in bowl to cool.
Heat oil, vinegar and sugar in pan until sugar is dissolved.
Put in blender.
Add soup, mustards, salt and pepper. Blend.
Pour over vegetables in bowl.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight to let flavors blend.
Tastes better after first day.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs enough to mix yolks and whites.
Add sugar, milk, salt and vanilla.
Heat 3/4 cup sugar slowly to make caramel. Pour caramel into custard cups to coat sides and bottom.
Pour in custard mixture.
Set the cups in a pan with hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake per directions or until slightly brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayo.
Add dry Ranch Dressing mix.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Spread with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: tava turkish stew
directions: Mix together oil, garlic and tomato sauce.
Cook hamburger until it turns grey; remove from heat and drain (dispose of grease).
Peel, chop and slice other ingredients.
Layer vegetables and meat.
Sprinkle with sauce.
Steam until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry onion and sausage; drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix soup and milk together.
Mix cheese and noodles together.
While warm, mix sausage and all other ingredients.
Crumble crackers on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country chicken 'n' biscuits
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine the chicken soup, milk and marjoram.
Stir in frozen chicken and vegetables.
Bring mixture to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 minutes. Meanwhile, tear cheese slices into several pieces.
Stir cheese into chicken mixture and cook until melted, then place the biscuits on top.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until biscuits are heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: calico chicken
directions: Brown chicken in shortening and drain.
Stir in soup, milk and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add Veg-All and parsley. Heat throughout.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and extracts together while warming milk.
Mix sugar in good with warm milk and other ingredinets and put into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then finish cooking at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake tuna and set aside.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles, tuna, celery and onion.
Blend in sour cream, thyme, mayonnaise mustard and salt.
Spoon 1/2 the mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 the zucchini.
Continue in layers and finally top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chopped tomato.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain shells. Brown beef and drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup into ground beef along with chilies, 1/2 cup grated cheese and onion.
Mix. Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stuff shells with meat.
Arrange shells in dish, pour remaining sauce over shells.
Then top with remaining cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes (cover for at least 30 minutes of baking time).

title: crumb top coffee cake
directions: Cut 1/4 cup margarine into flour and brown sugar until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, then reserve 1/2 cup for the topping.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat.
Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer until sauce is thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain. Rinse in cold water.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter
in
pan over low heat; add brown sugar and egg. Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar like pie crust.
Roll out and spread peanut butter as thick as you like.
Roll like jelly rolls and slice.
Put nuts on top if you like.

title: french beans with corn
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix with all other ingredients except margarine and crackers.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add, one at a time, eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add to batter.
Then when well mixed, put in chocolate chips.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers and add sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Mix well and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and beat until well mixed.
Pour over cracker crust.
Freeze until frozen.
Spread Cool Whip on chocolate mixture.
Chop Heath bars and sprinkle on Cool Whip.
Keep frozen until 20 minutes before serving.

title: mom zollner's plain cake
directions: Beat butters, egg yolks and sugar.
Add almond and lemon. Sift together flour and baking powder and add.
Beat egg whites and then fold into mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: carrot salad(shirley's)
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth with beater.
Add lemon and orange juices. Chill until partially set.
Add carrots and apples.
Place in mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with carrot curls and orange section, if desired, or serve plain.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with softened butter.
Pat out in large pan.
For first layer, mix 1/2 of Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
For second layer, mix pudding mix and milk together.
For third layer, top with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half stuffing mix in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: horseradish cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add other ingredients.
Store in a covered jar.
Serve on crackers.

title: paul's chicken for 2
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Spread Ranch dressing evenly on both pieces.
Sprinkle top with cheese and dill.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly and brown.

title: brazo mercedes
directions: Combine egg yolks and liberty condensada.
Cook on top of a double boiler.
Continue cooking until thick or of spreading consistency.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Set aside.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onions and bacon.
Add catsup, pork and beans, kidney beans, sugars, vinegar, mustard and salt. Mix well in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spicy lamb steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over steaks.
Refrigerate 2 hours, turning steaks every 20 minutes.
Broil 4 inches from heat, 6 minutes on each side for medium or 7 minutes for well done.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Pour off 3 tablespoons of fat.
Add onions and brown. Then add potatoes and water.
Cook covered for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in salt, soup and milk.
Heat but do not boil.
Garnish with bacon and parsley.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Mix
together
and drop over apples.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower or broccoli bake
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese; if too thick, thin with low-fat milk.
Pour over cooked vegetables.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Cook about 25 minutes in a 350° oven until cheese melts and is heated through.

title: beef casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook hamburger with salt and garlic salt; drain and set aside.
Drain the tomato juice into the hamburger. Cut the tomatoes into small pieces and add to the meat mixture.
Simmer 10-15 minutes.
Add the cooked rice and simmer until hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Pour French dressing over ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill for 15 minutes. Mix in mayonnaise.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: peanut and honey rolls
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey and powdered milk thoroughly.
Chill and roll into balls.
Then roll into graham cracker crumbs.
Keep chilled.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake half the cake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Melt caramels with milk and pour over the baked cake. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Pour rest of prepared cake mix over top and bake another 20 minutes.
Frost with desired icing when cooled.
Duncan Hines cake mix is suggested.
Serves 20.

title: molded cranberry party salad
directions: In saucepan combine 1 cup cold water, sugar and cranberries. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add remaining cold water, cranberry mixture and lemon juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini.
Put in microwave for one minute.
Scoop out zucchini.
Set scooped insides aside.
Saute onions and celery. Add stuffing mix and the scooped out portion of zucchini along with a little water until right consistency.
Stuff zucchini shell with this mixture.
Dot with butter and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Remove skin, cut into pieces.
Heat soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for 5 minutes. Soften tortillas in oil and drain.
Roll each with chicken and 2 tablespoons of soup mixture.
Pour soup over top.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Place margarine in a casserole dish in a 350° oven until melted.
Mix next three ingredients in a bowl.
When margarine is melted, pour the batter into center of the bowl. Do not stir. Then pour fruit and juices into center of batter.
Do not stir. Cook until brown and firm, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini in chicken broth.
Drain and chill. Chill other ingredients not ordinarily chilled. Drain olives, artichokes and mushrooms.
Combine tortellini, vegetables, Parmesan, pepperoni and dressing. Add 1/8 cup water to dressing bottle and shake. Add to salad and stir.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange potato slices in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
In bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in small amount of butter.
Allow to cook until onions are transparent.
Add chopped jalapeno peppers.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients, except crawfish.
Add cooked onions and peppers.
Stir in crawfish.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked and drained sausage.
Bake in oven until done at 350°.

title: cecil's stew
directions: Brown meat in oleo over medium heat.
Cover with water and cook 45 minutes.
Add celery, pepper, carrots and onion.
Cover with water and cook 1 hour.
Add potatoes, cover and cook 1 hour.
Test for seasoning.
Add onion soup and cook 20 minutes.
Add m.s.g. and more water, if needed.
Never cook fast.
Requires 4 hours of cooking on slow or simmer.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
For each cup, combine 1/4 cup mix to 3/4 cup boiling water.

title: chicken minestrone soup
directions: In a large soup pot, heat the chicken broth to boiling. Add the noodles and cook over medium heat for about 7 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and continue to cook over low heat for another 8 to 10 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed. You might want to add a little salt, if your broth is homemade. Store bought broth seems to be more salty.

title: two potato gratin
directions: Arrange half of russet potatoes in 8x8 inch glass baking dish. Sprinkle 1/4 of rosemary, salt and pepper.
Top with half of sweet potatoes.
Repeat rosemary, salt and pepper.
Repeat layering and season each layer.
Pour cream over.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave on High until potatoes are tender, about 18 minutes.
Sprinkle both cheeses over potatoes and microwave on high, uncovered until cheese melts and bubbles, about 3 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
May also be baked in oven at 350 degrees for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are tender.
Serves:

title: bubbles, bubbles, bubbles
directions: Put the ingredients in a container and shake well.
Allow to settle 4 hours before using.
Pour suds in a pan.
Dip wand into solution.
Slowly move wand through the air.
Watch the bubbles go!!
Have fun!!

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken pieces in seasoned flour and brown in margarine. Remove chicken, add remaining ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Place uncooked rice in the mixture.
Add chicken and pour remaining mixture over it.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil fryers; debone.
Spray large oblong casserole dish with Pam.
Place chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and cayenne pepper.
Dice onion; sprinkle over meat.
Add shredded Velveeta on top.
Crush half of the chips; put over cheese.
In blender, blend mushroom soup, chicken soup and Ro-Tel.
Pour over other ingredients; top with remaining chips which have been crushed.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Gradually add cream, stirring until smooth.
Spread butter in bottom of crust.
Pour in filling. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake for another 10 minutes.
Reduce again and bake until set.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix together sauce, mushrooms and pasta; set aside.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream; mix into pasta mixture.
Place in greased large casserole dish, cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes; uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth.
Stop blender often and push mixture toward blades with scraper.
Pack in 1/2 cup containers.
Refrigerate. Keep refrigerated.

title: potato casserole
directions: In top of double boiler, melt cheese. Add sour cream and onions. Set aside. Peel, slice and cook potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain well. Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste. Dot with margarine. Pour cheese sauce over potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: shirley maclaine's gourmet lamb stew
directions: Have butcher prepare lamb as follows:
Remove
fell and bone, trim off excess fat;
cut lamb into 1
1/2-inch
cubes. Heat lard or shortening in large skillet until
sizzling;
add lamb,	brown on	all sides until golden,
stirring.
Sprinkle flour over meat, cook a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, cook over very low heat until garlic begins
to smell. Add water (enough to barely cover meat), tomato paste, bouquet garni, salt and pepper. Cover; simmer about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until each is combined.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat one minute.
Fold in pineapple.
Transfer mixture to pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let pie cool.
Cover with Sour Cream Topping.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water.
Boil and pour over vegetables.
Add salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown battered cubed steak and place in casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup.
Fill empty can with water and add to fry pan drippings.
Add to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix a Betty Crocker fudge brownie mix as directed.
Put in a regular-size muffin tin.
Fill 2/3 full and press 1 small Reese's cup into the center.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: incredible nut mix
directions: Mix all together.
This recipe makes a lot.
Give as gifts packed in tins.
A great hostess gift!

title: holiday macaroons
directions: In a mixing bowl beat the eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly until thick and pale yellow.
Stir together dry ingredients; fold into egg mixture.
Stir in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheets.
Top with cherries.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites, and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Mix until all ingredients are well blended.
Stir in walnuts. Spread batter into prepared 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening and cheese. Stir in milk quickly. Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cinnamon stix
directions: Cream
oleo
and
sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Sift flour and cinnamon
together.
Stir
into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Place dough on 10 x 15-inch ungreased jelly roll pan.
Slightly beat egg white
and
brush
on
cookie dough.
(Sprinkle on pecans and press in
lightly,
optional.) Bake in 300° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cut into strips while warm.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Saute pepper, oregano, garlic, basil and Cajun seasoning.
Add sliced eggplant (unpeeled), sliced zucchini, sliced onion and sliced peppers.
Begin to cook and add chicken strips.
When food begins to liquify and soften, add ketchup, stewed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Vegetables should be soft before serving.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and milk alternately.
Add coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake slightly pulls away from sides of pan.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook and cool carrots.
Place carrots, onions and peppers in layers.
Mix next seven ingredients well.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Add peppers and bring to a boil.
Turn off unit and let mixture cool for 5 minutes.
Add liquid pectin and food coloring.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Invert for 30 seconds to one minute.
Makes 3 pints.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl; work in butter until breadcrumb consistency.
Add only enough water to hold together. Turn onto floured pastry board; shape into hands.
Roll out and place on cookie sheet; mark lightly.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup milk, 1 cup Bisquick and 1/2 stick margarine and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes its own crust!

title: heather ray's delicious popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in microwave for 4 minutes on High.
When finished, serve with Mt. Dew.
Makes a scrumptious snack.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread marshmallows across bottom.
Combine strawberries and their juice with dry jello and set aside.
Mix cake mix according to package directions, pour over the marshmallows.
Spoon berry mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes more.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Melt butter and grated cheese in double boiler.
Put pimiento, pepper and macaroni through a coarse food chopper.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a pan of water at 275° for 2 hours.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix well and pour batter on 2 large cookie sheets lined with foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place on clean towel to cool.
Remove foil.
Mix 5 tablespoons flour and 1 cup milk; cook on medium heat until thickened, then cool in refrigerator.
In another bowl, cream 1 cup powdered sugar with 1/2 cup Crisco and 1 stick butter, add cooled flour paste and mix well.
More sugar may be needed to thicken.
Put between layers and chill cake in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a heavy pot, heat the whole milk and salt to simmering, then add the rice.
Continue simmering (stirring often) for about 40 minutes, until the rice is tender.
Cover when cooking.
(If you wish to add raisins, do so now and cook for another 5 minutes.)
In a bowl, beat the eggs, white sugar, vanilla, evaporated milk and lemon juice with a wire whisk.
Blend several large spoonfuls of the cooked rice mixture into the bowl (eggs, etc.).
Stir.
Repeat several times.
Pour all of the egg mixture into the pot of rice; cook slowly until it becomes thick.
Stir often.
Take off the heat.
Pour out of the hot pot into a bowl. Stir often while cooling (so it does not separate).
Sprinkle the top with either cinnamon or nutmeg.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken vicenza
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Drain and remove to platter (keep warm in oven).
Saute onions in oil until transparent.
Add tomatoes and simmer, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Return chicken to sauce, add other ingredients except sherry.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes (turn chicken occasionally).
Stir in sherry and cook 5 minutes more.
(Is good served with rice.)

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and jello over low heat.
(No water.) Stir often. Cool until partly set. Fold in the whipped cream or Cool Whip.
May add the nuts.

title: egg cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Spray tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar, vanilla and water; mix.
Sift flour and salt; add to mixture.
Mix.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly.
Using a small portion of the mixture about the size of a walnut, roll longways into a crescent shape (keep size even).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool slightly.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together the margarine and flour.
Add the nuts and press on bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: honey glazed snack
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
In large bowl, mix cereal and nuts.
Mix margarine and honey.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss to coat. Spread on 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: old fashion tea cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll on floured rolling board to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt butter and mix spices. Mix all other ingredients and pour butter and spice mixture over it. Mix well. Bake at 250° for 2 hours; check often.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with 8 ounces of Cool Whip.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Bring water to boil; remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add crushed strawberries; refrigerate until partially jelled.
Break the cake into small pieces.
Add to mixture; pour in tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam and press and chill.
Can eat with whipped cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix simmering for 15 minutes.
Pour in baking dish. Top with strips of bacon or cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Great for picnics.

title: casserole beef stew
directions: Mix together salt, sugar and tapioca.
Sprinkle over layer of meat and vegetables.
Pour V-8 juice over all.
Cover and bake for 6 hours at 250° or place in crock-pot for 8 hours on low.

title: apple walnut stuffing
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon, cook until bouillon dissolves. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and add celery mixture.
Mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting. Place remaining stuffing in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot.

title: watermelon fruit boat
directions: Cut top third lengthwise from watermelon; cover and refrigerate to use as desired.
Scoop balls from larger section of watermelon.
Remove seeds; cover balls and refrigerate.
Scoop remaining pulp from watermelon with large spoon to form shell. (For decorative edge on shell, cut a scalloped or saw-toothed design.)
Drain shell. Cut thin slice from bottom of shell to keep it from tipping over; refrigerate.
Scoop melon balls from cantaloupe and honeydew.
Mix together, cover and refrigerate. Just before serving, slice peaches.
Drain melon balls.
Mix all fruit into watermelon shell and garnish with mint, if desired. Serve immediately.
Yields 20 servings.

title: burger delight
directions: Fry onion and burger until brown.
Add corn and soup.
Cook egg noodles separately until tender and combine with burger mixture.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make crust of graham crackers and melted butter, enough to make good base for filling.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add sugar and cream cheese.
Whip with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and let cool, then add the whipped cream in Jell-O mixture and sprinkle a little of the graham crackers on top and chill for several hours.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake in 11 x 15-inch well-greased pan in 325° oven about 25 minutes.
Burns easily.
Partly cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry glace tart
directions: Roll crust out on lightly floured surface.
Transfer floured side down into a 9-inch tart pan with removable bottom; press pastry up sides.
Trim excess.
Prick bottom with fork; bake until golden in 450° oven and let cool.
In a medium saucepan, crush 2 cups berries; add 3/4 cup grape juice and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 minutes.
Sieve berry mixture, discarding the pulp.
Measure 1 1/4 cups of mixture; return to saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and remaining grape juice; add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Equal.
Spread about 1/4 of mixture over the bottom and sides of cooled pie shell.
Arrange half of whole berries, stem end down, in shell.
Spoon half of the remaining mixture over the berries, making sure they are all well covered.
Arrange remaining strawberries over first layer, topping with remaining mixture.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients but chicken.
Dissolve 2 chicken bouillon cubes in hot water.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter. Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put rice mixture on bottom and chicken on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour or until done (total about 1 1/2 hours).
Add a little water if dry.
Put foil on top if too brown.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls on ungreased cookie sheet, pressing all squares together.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 350°.
Chill.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple and peaches.
Mix all ingredients except topping.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place in pie crust and chill.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut strawberries into 1/2-inch pieces. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside.

title: oven panfish
directions: Mix the parsley
and
shallots together and sprinkle on the bottom of a Pyrex
baking
dish.
Put
the fish on top and pour the wine over
it.	Mix the breadcrumbs, salt, pepper and cayenne; sprinkle over
fish.
Set
mushrooms
on
top and dot with butter, if	desired.
Sprinkle
dill
seed	over fillets. Bake, uncovered, in a 500°
oven
for 5 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes.	Baste fish with pan juices.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and oleo.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat with wire whip until all cheese is melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar to taste.
Dot with butter and sprinkle cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef well and drain off excess grease. Melt cheese in medium saucepan. Add ground meat, Ro-Tel tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder and stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm with chips.

title: swordfish on skewers
directions: You will need 8 long rosemary branches or wooden skewers.
If using wooden skewers, soak in water for 15 minutes (to prevent burning).

title: cut green beans
directions: Add fresh water almost to top of beans.
Add seasoning and salt.
Cook until water is low, for about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes if desired about 1/2 way through cooking.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut each wing into 2 pieces. In a large deep skillet, heat oil over moderate heat (365°). Fry wings for 5 minutes.
Transfer to paper towel. In pie plate, combine butter, vinegar and cayenne pepper. Add wings; toss to coat.
Arrange on warm platter. In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients and serve with wings. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat at low speed 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute. Turn batter into two 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Core and wash peppers.
Place in water to cover and boil 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Prepare dressing bread.
Stuff peppers with dressing bread.
Mash tomatoes and place on stuffed peppers.
Use the tomato to pour over and around peppers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork; stir in oil, vanilla and rind.
Blend in sugar until thickened.
Measure flour; blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil; turn down heat and simmer about 5 minutes and cool.
In a large bowl, cream margarine, sugars and eggs.
Add soda mixed in 1/3 cup of raisin juice, flour, oatmeal, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger french bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cut loaf of French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread meat mixture evenly over top of buttered bread.
Wrap with foil around bread, leaving top (meat), uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with cheese strips.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Unwrap and cut in slices.

title: celery root-potato puree
directions: Peel celery roots and potatoes.
Cut both into equal size quarters.
Boil until soft.
Drain and place in mixing bowl.
Add butter, buttermilk and half of the cream.
Mix until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve this instead of regular mashed potatoes for a new twist!

title: summertime strawberry cake
directions: Punch holes in cooled cake.
Pour hot jello over cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Slice strawberries; use on top of cake.
Add a layer of Cool Whip, then add whole strawberry on top.
A refreshing cake for summer.

title: jelly
directions: Cook ingredients for 10 minutes and put in jars.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Cook all day in crock-pot on medium heat.
Delicious with rice or creamed potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine fish and rice; mix well.
Stir in defrosted soup (add more soup if you like things moist).
Pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick hopping john
directions: The proportions are up to you!

title: rocky road candy
directions: Put on low fire or double boiler first three ingredients until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add marshmallows; stir gently until all marshmallows are coated.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper; chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Put the molasses, sugar and vinegar in a pan and boil until the mixture hardens when dropped into cold water.
Add the vanilla.
Pour mixture into a buttered pan.
Mark into squares and set aside to cool.
Nuts and/or coconut can be placed in the bottom of the buttered pan before pouring in the taffy.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break the angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Put into bottom of trifle cake bowl. Put layer of strawberries, peaches and blueberries.
Put instant pudding on that.
Do two layers of this. Then finish off with Cool Whip.
Garnish with kiwi.
This is a low calorie dessert.

title: fide's chile colorado(authentic)
directions: Boil chiles and tomatillos for 5 minutes.
Cut up the meat in small chunks.
Brown until done in a large skillet with lard. Blend chiles, tomatillos, garlic, 1/2 cup water and salt.
Pour blended mixture over meat and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole with onions
directions: Cook frozen beans per directions on package; drain (or use French-style in can and drain).
Combine cooked frozen or canned beans, mushroom soup, pimiento and lemon juice.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Also can mix onions in casserole if you like, too.
Continue baking, uncovered, about 5 minutes more or until onions are heated through.
This will serve 6 people.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger meat and drain well.
Add onions, bell peppers and celery.
Blend well.
Add half of tomato juice and all tomato paste.
Slowly cook for 25 minutes.
Add all herbs, salt, black pepper and rest of tomato juice.
Add enough water to thin out. Turn heat to low and stir regularly.
Let cook for approximately 35 minutes.
Watch carefully; don't let stick.

title: steamed ground pork
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well; then place in a greased pan with cover.
Let cook over hot fire for 15 minutes. Allow to steam.
Extra good!!

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple with dry pudding. (Chill while cake bakes.) Cool cake. Add Cool Whip to pineapple mixture. Frost between layers and frost cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9-inch square pan as listed from top to bottom in order.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend together	the
ingredients.
If
too moist, add a little powdered sugar; if too dry, add a little corn syrup and peanut butter.
Roll
mixture
into
small
size balls.
Place ball into center
of the miniature size cupcake papers.
Melt chocolate and pour
into	cups
to fill.	May need to add some paraffin wax to chocolate (size of a walnut).
Yield: approximately 50 cups.

title: mexican pizza pie
directions: This recipe makes 2 good-sized platters.
I usually only make 1/2 of the recipe.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Grease pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Spread in pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: fun and easy salsa
directions: Add tomatoes,
onions and green pepper to your favorite salsa. Mix
all
together before serving.
Everyone will love it.

title: one dish meal
directions: In casserole, place 1 layer sliced raw potatoes, 1 layer sliced onion, 1 cup cooked rice and 1 layer hamburger.
Season each layer with salt.
Pour in tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Prepare cake from first 5 ingredients.
Bake in oiled and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: romano chix bites
directions: Cut chicken into large pieces.
Mix eggs, milk oregano, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Pan-fry chicken in lightly oiled pan for 2 minutes each side.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Romano cheese and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Remove peels from cooked sweet potatoes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Melt the butter or oleo in a large frying pan.
Add sugar and stir until it melts. Add water and bring to a boil.
Lay sweet potatoes in syrup and cook slowly, turning slices so both sides brown evenly.

title: parmesan-paprika potatoes(microwave quick!)
directions: Wash and remove eyes from the potatoes. Place in medium size serving bowl or small casserole.
Microwave 10 minutes. Check for doneness.

Using a fork and sharp knife, slice the potatoes in the serving bowl. Add all other ingredients and continue cutting through the potatoes with knife and mixing with the fork until a nice chunky, "buttery" look is achieved.
(It happens very quickly.) Roundly shape the top a little and garnish with paprika and parsley flakes.
Serves 2.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together real good and roll into 2 to 3 rolls. Wrap in aluminum foil with shiny side toward meat. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Punch holes in bottom of rolls with fork. Place on rack in baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: fast and easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well. Place 1/2 noodles in casserole dish. Layer ground beef, Ricotta cheese, spaghetti sauce and shredded Cheddar cheese, then
another layer of noodles, Ricotta, ground beef, sauce and Cheddar cheese. Cook at 375° for 45 minutes until bubbly. Serve with French loaf bread.

title: baked salmon
directions: Wash salmon inside and out.
Be sure to wash away blood in the spinal vein on the inside.
Scrape the outside of the salmon under running water to wash.
Dry the salmon inside and out.

title: senator barb's spicy bay recipe
directions: Pick over crab meat.
Remove crust from bread and break bread into small pieces.
Mix bread with beaten egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into cakes and saute quickly in a small amount of fat.
(Cakes can also be broiled.)
Serves 6 people.

title: peppy chicken
directions: In a covered container, shake cornstarch and water for 30 seconds; set aside.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil.
Saut chicken, garlic and onions until chicken is browned.
Add broccoli, peppers and sauces until mixture thickens by stirring contents.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add zucchini, dry ingredients and nuts to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pans (1 tube pan or 2 loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crock pot deer stew
directions: Layer potatoes, then carrots in bottom of crock pot.
