Top with meat; sprinkle meat with soy sauce, salt, paprika, pepper and flour.
Spread with chopped onions.
Combine beef broth and tomato sauce and pour over all.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add beer.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: turnip greens and smoked turkey
directions: In a pot, bring 3 cups of water to a boil. Add vinegar and salt. While this is boiling, in another saucepan, melt butter and caramelized sugar, then add onion, garlic, jalapeno pepper, honey and turkey. Stir. Add this mixture to boiling water along with greens and cook 15 to 20 minutes until greens reach your desired tenderness.

title: crunchy taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and break into small pieces.
Carefully drain off fat and let cool.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces in a large bowl.
Then add the onion, tomato, cheese and the ground beef.
Mix well.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl; add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas and spoon into three 9-inch well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and remove to cool completely.

title: lemon pie
directions: Add butter, remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add beaten egg yolks, rind and juice of lemon; mix well.

title: tuna and chips casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Empty soup into 1 quart casserole dish. Mix in milk.
Put potato chips between sheets of wax paper.
Crush chips with a rolling pin.
Repeat until you have 1 1/4 cups crushed chips.
Drain tuna and add. Also add 1 cup of potato chips and peas.
Mix gently.
Sprinkle top with remaining one-quarter cup chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave cooking)
directions: Preparation:
Wash and remove any wilted outside leaves. Shred or cut into wedges.

title: john's cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder, brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheets.
Serve warm.
Yields 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and egg, stirring until moistened.
Set aside.

title: cornflake chews
directions: Put cornflakes in a greased bowl.
Bring to a boil white sugar and white syrup.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well and pour over cornflakes.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice. Make a well in dry ingredients, add oil, eggs, strawberries and mix. Add nuts. Pour mixture into 3 (greased and floured) loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix honey and mustard together.
Cut each breast in half.
Coat breast in honey and mustard mixture.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Bake on an aluminum foil lined baking sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Combine pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Bring to boiling point.
Add cornstarch that has been dissolved in water.
Cook until thick and clear; remove from fire.
Combine egg whites and first 1/4 cup of sugar.
Beat until dry and stiff.
Gradually add the other 1/4 cup of sugar and beat until sugar is dissolved.
Fold pineapple mixture, that is still warm, into egg mixture.
Add lemon juice.

title: german style pork steaks
directions: Salt and pepper black ribs to taste.
Place in "roast-in-bag" (hole in top), wrapped in heavy foil.
Put over coals and cover with big pot.
Heat for 45 minutes.
Take out of bag, then grill with basting of mustard sauce on both sides.
Place back in foil and heat on back of grill until ready to serve.

title: round steak parmesan
directions: Combine egg and water; combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into Parmesan cheese mixture.
In a large skillet, brown coated meat in oil.
Transfer to a greased shallow casserole.
In same skillet, cook onion until soft.
Stir in salt, pepper, sugar, marjoram and tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Uncover and top with cheese slices.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: soy chicken
directions: Very easy!!
Make 3 slices across the top of chicken.
Pour the soy sauce over the chicken, using approximately 1/2 to 1 cup of soy sauce.
Sprinkle a good amount of garlic powder over the top.
Let sit for 15 to 20 minutes.
Best if barbecued on gas grill.
Also can broil.

title: christmas holly-leaf cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter.
Add about 6 to 7 drops of green food coloring.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix thoroughly.
Form 1 teaspoon in a leaf shape on butter-greased wax paper.
Dot with 3 red candies.
(Bowl may be kept over a pan of hot water.)
Cool on wax paper and keep in a cool place about 2 days.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until fork easily pierces potatoes.
Cool slightly; remove skins and place into large mixing bowl.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix in nutmeg, salt and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in comes out clean.

title: sweet and spicy curry goat
directions: Over medium heat, saute chopped garlic, onion and soy sauce in oil until lightly browned.
Add stew meat and brown lightly.
Add milk and curry powder.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add honey and cumin. Stir.
Reduce heat to low and add remaining ingredients.
Continue to cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine and roll in crushed chips. Sprinkle with garlic salt and place in buttered pan, skin side up. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: real fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: sauce(for pork roast or chicken)
directions: Cook onion, oil and water until onion is tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
This will keep for a long time if refrigerated.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla.
Stir in the pineapple, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese in medium mixing bowl until smooth.
Slowly add marshmallow cream, whipping after each addition.
When this is smooth, add Cool Whip and whip until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Put in pie pan.
Put salt, flour, sugar and spices in a bowl.
Melt butter in saucepan and pour over mixture in bowl.
Mix with fork.
Spoon mixture over apples in pan, covering completely.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until apples are soft.
Serve topped with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter; form into balls.
Place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips; add 1 teaspoon vegetable oil. Using toothpicks, dip balls in chocolate; let dry on wax paper.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups (2 1/2-inches).
In a medium saucepan, melt corn oil spread.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except croutons and cheese.
Cook until onions are soft.
Serve in soup bowls topped with croutons and cheese.

title: zella's sweet pickles from dill pickles
directions: Drain the dill pickles.
If small, slice in half across; if bigger, quarter them.
Put back in jars.
In a saucepan, bring the sugar and vinegar to a good boil.
Pour over the pickles right away.
Put lid on and let stand until cool, then refrigerate. The pickles get nice and crisp and are ready to eat in a day or two.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage real fine.
Put in bottom of baking dish.
Cook hamburger in skillet until brown.
Mix tomato soup and 1/2 soup can of water; add to ground beef mixture.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: marie's favorite meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add beaten egg, bread crumbs, dry powdered milk, onion, salt and basil. Add beef and mix well.
Pat mixture into loaf pan or shape into loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: steak supper in foil package
directions: Place meat in
x 18-inch foil or roasting pan.
Top with onion soup and mushroom soup.
Place carrots and potatoes around. Sprinkle with
water
and
seal the foil.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 450°.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar, shortening or butter, eggs and vanilla and lemon flavoring. Beat 2 1/2 minutes on high speed.
Turn to low speed.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk.
Beat about 2 1/2 minutes.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl; shape into small round balls. Mix sugar and cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Roll each ball of cookie dough in sugar and cinnamon, then press lightly onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a dish or mold; chill.
This will freeze well.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat sugar into eggs gradually.
Stir in next 6 ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: saucy party meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Combine 16 ounce can cranberry sauce in large saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Add remaining can of cranberry sauce; heat thoroughly.
Transfer to chafing dish and keep warm.
(I heat and serve mine in a crock-pot.)

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar. Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until set.

title: boo boo's fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, put the rice, 5 cups water, butter, onion soup mix, chopped onion, mushrooms, beef bouillon cubes and garlic powder.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes, or put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
After rice is tender, remove from heat and put in 2 tablespoons Gravy Master, which will make the rice dark.
Rinse large package of bean sprouts under hot water, then add to rice mixture and mix. Add in bamboo shoots and pineapple (drained) and cherries, if desired.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Grease baking dish.
Crush graham cracker crumbs on bottom and top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add the next 4 ingredients and mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each rectangle.
Put 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture, twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush top with reserved 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Place in large bowl.
Add cucumber, green pepper and onion; mix well.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Pour over macaroni and toss until well coated.
Add egg.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours.
Garnish with pepper strips and cherry tomatoes and serve.

title: creamy black bean soup
directions: Puree all ingredients but onions in blender or food processor. Serve cold with onions and extra yogurt as garnish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: You will need a medium size saucepan and wax paper.

title: peanut butter balls(like reese's)
directions: Mix and form in small balls.
Roll in melted dipping chocolate.

title: granola bars
directions: Stir and heat honey and peanut butter in large saucepan until melted.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, raisins, carrots and coconut.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press together firmly.
Cut into squares.

title: cold spanish soup
directions: Mash tomatoes.	Add
water,
cucumber and onion.
Blend in French
dressing and mint leaves.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in a flat soup plate with 2 ice cubes in each portion.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Beat together and pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sure looks like pie but they call it reba's cheese cake
directions: In mixer bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour in prepared crust.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with your favorite fruit.

title: vanilla snaps
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beaten egg and cream well. Add vanilla and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Thoroughly chill.
Toss 1/4 of dough on floured board and roll as thin as possible.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into 12 greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly brown.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Beat with mixer.
Put in pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips on top.
Chill again.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Beat eggs; add last.
Bake at 350° for 38 minutes.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender. Drain. Mash potatoes in large bowl with electric mixer. Add softened cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic. Beat at high speed until smooth. Spoon into lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chilled chicken macaroni
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in cooked macaroni, vegetables and olives or relish.
Drain the chicken.
Mash with fork and stir in.
Leftover cooked chicken is even better.
Chill 4 hours and serve.

title: applesauce-raisin snack cake
directions: Place raisins and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain raisins, discarding water.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine applesauce and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add flour mixture to applesauce mixture, stirring until blended; fold in raisins.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soften yeast with sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Beat the eggs.
Add the lukewarm milk; add yeast and sugar mixture.
Add half the flour, then mix thoroughly.
Add the melted shortening and beat well.
Add balance of flour or enough to make a soft dough.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Grind nuts, cranberries, oranges and celery.
Make jello and add all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both kinds of sugar together. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture to make a dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately after removing cookies from the oven, press a miniature peanut butter cup into the center of each cookie until only the top of the peanut butter cup shows.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then remove from muffin tins.
Store in airtight containers.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Add apples and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 350 degrees 50 to 55 minutes.

title: seafood delight salmon cakes
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Form into patties.
Using a large skillet sprayed with Pam, cook until golden brown on both sides. Be sure to press and flip.

title: cheerios nuggets
directions: *Substitution:
Package of trail mix in place of raisins and peanuts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain 1 can of the peaches.
Mix remaining ingredients and set aside.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Make white sauce in a double boiler using the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.

title: butter pecan ice cream torte
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix milk with pudding and beat approximately 2 minutes.
Add softened ice cream and mix.
Press 1/2 of the crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour ice cream mixture on top of crust.
Spread entire tub of Cool Whip on top of ice cream.
Sprinkle rest of cracker crumbs on top and freeze.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine the next 6 ingredients. Spread over the potatoes.
Top with herb dressing that has been mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp muffins
directions: Bind together with mayonnaise.
Pile on halved English muffins.
Broil 2 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Use 12-inch circle dish.
Spread bean dip.
Mix sour cream with 1/2 taco seasoning; taste, can add more.
Spread over bean dip.
Drain just a little of the salsa and spread over sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top and garnish with green onion.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well. Add in taco mix, tomato sauce, beans and picante sauce.
Place a layer of tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add half meat sauce mixture.
Top with half of the cheese.
Layer again with tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Mix soup with milk until smooth and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-filled salisbury steaks
directions: In a medium bowl, mix lightly but thoroughly the beef, crumbs, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Shape
into 4 oval patties. Enclose a cheese stick in each patty, covering cheese completely. Brown patties in a little butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Remove meat and add broth and water to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Return patties and surround with onions.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove meat.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine oil, egg and milk in one bowl.
In another bowl, add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle Spicy Topping over the top, then bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
In separate bowl, combine remaining milk (1/4 cup), cake mix and oleo; mix well. Press half of the cake mixture into the bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove "crust." Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Drizzle with caramel mixture.
Top with remaining cake mixture and gently press into caramel.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cut before completely cooled.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: You will also need a turkey bag and nonstick Pam.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; shred meat.
Cook rice as directed on package. Saute onions in butter; blend in flour, soup and milk for sauce. Add mushrooms.
In a large casserole, alternate layers of sauce, rice, chicken and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 300° to 350° until bubbly, 30 to 40 minutes.
If desired, add sliced water chestnuts in layering.
Serves 12 to 14.
Can be divided into several smaller casserole dishes and frozen.

title: stuffed angel food cake filling, custard pie filling or banana
directions: *Use 1 large can; measure 1 1/2 cups milk and dilute with 1/2 cup water.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Butter a 9 X 13 pan.
Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine. Spread and press into pan.
Refrigerate (or bake at 375° for 8 minutes and cool).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix the soda, flour and sugar.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the first mixture.
Grease and flour flat pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: a&w coney sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer until thick for about 1 hour. Put on hot dogs.

title: peach jam
directions: Mash peaches.
Grind oranges (about 2) fine in food chopper. Add orange rind. Chop cherries in juice in blender until fine. Mix all together to make 5 cups. Mix Sure-Jell with fruit mixture. Bring to a hard boil.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Pour into sterilized jelly jars. Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: garlic and bread sauce
directions: Place garlic, bread crumbs and salt into a mortar and pound to a paste. Gradually add enough vinegar to dilute the paste to the consistency of thick cream. Serve on crackers.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in pan (I use and it's best to use a black iron frypan).
Add stick margarine.
Cut margarine and cook over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 240°.
If you don't have a thermometer, bring to a boil and boil for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Cut into squares when hardened.

title: crowd pleasing potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Separate eggs.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion; toss gently.
In another bowl, mash yolks with salad dressing.
Cream vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt; pour over potatoes and stir to coat.
Cover and chill.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: eastern shore sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, milk, eggs and sugar.
Beat at high speed with mixer.
Add flavorings.
Mix baking powder with 1 tablespoon milk and add to the potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: cinnamon flip
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk, egg, flour and baking powder.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth mixture in pan with spatula.
Sift a sprinkling of flour over top.
Dab with butter and brown sugar cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: best ever hash brown casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Put half of the mixture into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle with the sausage.
Cover with the remaining potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: flying high ham and noodles casserole
directions: Saute onions and ham just till onions are tender.
Add soup, milk, sour cream, mustard and pepper.
Mix sauce, ham and noodles. Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkled with toasted almonds and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and squeeze to remove moisture.
Mix all ingredients; roll into balls.
May be frozen before baking.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 24 minutes.
Will keep frozen up to 6 months.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine spaghetti sauce and meat; simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine oregano, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.

title: salsa dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese until smooth.
Add salsa until desired consistency.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers in red or green bell pepper or serving bowl.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour, salt and spices.
Cut in butter to form pea sized pieces.
Place apples in large bowl and coat with sugar mixture.
Place apples in pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes.
Bake another 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: spicy harvest pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine apples, squash, carrots, nuts and flour.
Toss to coat.
In medium bowl, beat margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, lemon juice, vanilla, orange peel and eggs; blend well. Combine contents of both bowls; mix well.
Spoon filling into pie shells.

title: samoa rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in heavy skillet. Add uncooked rice. Cook, stirring frequently, until rice is golden. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
In large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups cheese, beans, sauces and chips.
Add meat and mix lightly.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spread top with sour cream and 1/2 cup more cheese.
Circle reserved chips around edge and bake 5 minutes more.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onions to liking.
Drain and add to rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: chicken the easy way
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
In a separate dish, mix all remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: foil baked fish
directions: Place each fish portion in center of a 12-inch square of foil. Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put carrot and onion on fish.
Seal foil.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Fold back foil and sprinkle fish with parsley.
Serve in foil.

title: diabetic angel macaroons
directions: Cover baking sheet with aluminum foil.
In large bowl, beat cake mix, carbonated beverage and extracts on low speed for about 30 seconds, then at medium speed for 1
minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: jalapeno cheese balls
directions: Combine cheese, peppers, onion and garlic in work bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade.
Process with 2 or 3 on-off turns to blend.
Add mayonnaise; process until smooth.
Chill until firm.
Form into 1 large ball or 16 to 20 bite sized balls. Chill until cheese is firm.
Roll in pecans; chill again.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easter coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; add to cream mix. Stir in vanilla and sour cream. Spread 1/2 batter into 9 x 13 pan. Mix brown sugar, white sugar and pecans. Pour 1/2 over batter in pan; add remaining batter and then remaining topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: perie's creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, in double boiler. (If careful and stir can use saucepan.)
Bring to boil.
Add chicken broth, broccoli and carrots.
Cook (do not boil) over low heat, about 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Melt oleo.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In medium size bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar and salt.
Add the oleo and yeast water.
Stir in flour; cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Divide dough in 3 parts; roll out in a circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted oleo.
Cut in 12 wedges.
Roll up from big end to point; put on greased sheet and let rise 4 hours.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.
Fry.
Place in a pan and cook over 1 hour at 350°.
Pour 1 can beef gravy over.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning packet.
Spread bean dip on platter. Top with avocado mixture, followed by sour cream mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients on top.

title: low-fat orange milk shake
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds or until smooth. Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade chocolates
directions: Mix powdered sugar and coconut in large pan.
Add milk.
Using hands, mix until well blended.
Roll mixture into marble size balls.
Place on cookie sheets and refrigerate for one day.
Place paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir until chips are melted.
Insert toothpicks into balls.
Dip in warm mixture to coat.
Place on wax paper to cool candy.
Keeps well and makes about 180 balls.

title: cheese pineapple bake
directions: Layer pineapple in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with sugar and flour mixture.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over casserole. Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of wheat bread
directions: Combine Cream of Wheat, Bisquick and cooking oil.
Add milk and stir.
Bake in iron skillet at 450° until brown.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water together.
Drain pineapple.
Add to Jell-O. Add the frozen strawberries.
Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan and refrigerate until firm.
Take the sour cream and spread on firm Jell-O. Top with the other half of the Jell-O and refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, slightly beaten; pour scalded milk over mixture.
Cook 15 minutes in a double boiler or until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.
Bake until medium brown.

title: stuffed pickles
directions: Core center of pickles and stuff with braunschweiger.
Chill several hours.
Slice stuffed pickles and serve with picks.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well and pour over popped corn in bowl large enough to mix well.
Coat popped corn evenly.
Divide onto 2 large cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir popped corn every 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through apples.
Heap up in pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust, seal, flute and slit.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: date balls(cookies)
directions: Cook until thick and dates are mushy.
Stir in 3 cups Rice Krispies.
Make in ball and roll in powdered sugar, coconut or chopped nuts.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: lemon lime jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
Cool.
Poke holes into cake with fork.
Dissolve Jell-O into hot water; spoon over holes in cake.
Mix the last 4 ingredients to make topping.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: hot dog relish(14 pints; very good)
directions: Heat to boiling and simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in jars immediately.

title: almond buffet casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and soup to a boil.
Add rice; cover and reduce heat and boil for 25 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Fry sausage until brown.
Remove meat and pour off fat.
Add celery, onion and green pepper to remaining fat in pan and cover until tender and crisp.
Add rice, cooked sausage and 1/2 cup of the almonds to vegetables.
Reserve remainder for garnish.
Mix well; pour into 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle remaining almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: caramel apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter or margarine.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Sprinkle over pie filling and bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or serve warm with coffee cream.

title: pop-up bread
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Warm water, milk and oil.
Add to flour/yeast mixture and beat well with mixer.
Add eggs, salt and sugar and beat.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until elastic.
Pour into two (1 pound) greased coffee cans.
Put plastic tops on and let rise until it touches the top, 1 hour or longer.
Remove the top of the can (hence the name).
Let stand for 15 minutes on wire rack then remove from can.
Slice and enjoy!

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Chill.

title: baked sausages with peppers
directions: Poke the sausages with a fork in a few places.
Slice potatoes and onions.
Cut peppers into strips.
In a large pan, layer potatoes, onions and peppers.
Place sausages on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with oregano and pepper.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are cooked.
Sprinkle green onions over top before serving.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add salsa and mix thoroughly.
Store in the refrigerator overnight.

title: tunaburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix tuna, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Fill buns with tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder together for batter. Melt butter in 2 qt. round or oval baking dish. Pour in batter over butter, but do not stir together. Spread fruit pie filling on top. Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: low-fat easy turkey gravy
directions: Lightly coat a medium saucepan with nonstick cooking spray. Add onion and celery and cook over medium heat until tender (about 5 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables in pan and stir until flour is browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in turkey or chicken broth and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Strain to remove vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: celery spread
directions: Mix well and fill 3 celery pieces.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place browned hamburger on bottom of pan and layer of drained potatoes and layer of cheese.
Repeat one time.
Heat at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat in small amount of oil.
Remove excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese and sour cream.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, about 4 tablespoons at a time.
Mix will be very thick.
Sprinkle in salt and slowly stir in milk.
Return to stove top and bring to boil over medium-low heat so to dissolve well. Stir often.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Will thicken as it cools; serve over ice cream.
Store in glass jar with lid in refrigerator.
Will last quite a while.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, water and raisins in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cook at High 4 minutes.
Stir well and cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir again and cook 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in sour cream, blending well.
Pour in baked pie shell.
When cool, garnish with Cool Whip.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit.
Mix all ingredients with sour cream. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: cranberry supreme salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Sprinkle with sugar and let drain overnight (use juice for fruit punch).
Cut grapes in half and remove seeds.
Add grapes and nuts to well-drained cranberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and mound in lettuce cups to serve.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Bake until light brown (about 12 minutes).
Crumble with spoon.
Cool.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs.
Press remaining crumbs evenly in bottom of pan.
Pack ice cream on crumbs. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Wrap and refreeze.

title: french stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large, covered crock-pot.
Cook for 8 to 10 hours on low.
Serves 8 to 12.
Freezes well.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut tortilla shells into one-inch squares.
Bring stock to a boil.
Drop the tortilla squares into stock, one at a time.
Boil for 30 minutes at 250° to 300°.
Add chicken and simmer for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on cubes, then cover with flour and braise in a fairly deep pot until browned.
Add some water, then gravy.
Bring to a boil and allow to simmer with mushrooms, onions and seasoning for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese as desired and bake uncovered for another 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well. Store in jars or other airtight containers.
When ready to serve, mix 1/3 cup mix with 2/3 cup hot water.

title: homemade chocolate syrup
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Gradually add water until mixture is smooth.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil and allow to boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Allow to cool and cover and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups syrup (16 ounces).

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage and sprinkle into pie shells evenly.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage and cheese, being careful not to overflow.

title: sharon's lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease baking sheets. Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and lemon juice in large bowl. Beat on low speed until well blended. Add nuts. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 1-inch apart on prepared baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute on baking sheets. Remove to cooling racks. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large bowl at high speed.
Add one egg at a time; beat well after each.
Add sugar.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until blended.
Pour batter into greased (10 inch) tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 - 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours. Remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix next first ingredients together and then add to first mixture.
Add nuts if desired. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves (9 x 5 x 3-inch).

title: red dot turnips
directions: Cook turnips in small amount of boiling salted water until tender, about 12 minutes.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss lightly with turnips.
Makes 5 servings.

title: herb drop cookies(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in molasses.
Sift together flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add alternately with coffee to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in anise and coriander.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix pancake batter, sugar, baking powder and 1 stick of margarine.
Set aside.

title: parsnip stew
directions: Fry out pork in kettle.
Add small sliced onion, layer of sliced potatoes and layer of sliced parsnips.
Cook in small amount of water.

title: cheesy mac chili
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, celery, macaroni, chili powder and salt. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until celery and macaroni are tender.
Stir in kidney beans. Simmer until thoroughly heated.
Spoon chili into serving bowls. Cut cheese slices into 4 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Devein and clean shrimp; saute in oil until they turn pink. Add onion, garlic and green pepper; saute.
Add parsley, tomato sauce, ketchup, bay leaf, cooking wine, salt, pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes. Serve over white rice.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together first three ingredients.
Melt margarine, add cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over first three ingredients.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix with spoon. Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant parmigiano
directions: Slice eggplant, dip in egg, then in breadcrumbs; fry in oil. Drain well on paper towels.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer ingredients: eggplant, cheese and sauce.
Heat in oven at 425° until bubbly or cheese melts.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Spread in a long glass dish. Chop onion small; sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of grated cheese on top of that.
Chop bell pepper; spread on top of onion layer.
Dice 1 tomato; spread on top of bell pepper, then sprinkle the other half package of grated cheese on top.
Dip Doritos, nachos or your favorite chip.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine 1/3 cup of milk with cake mix and oleo.
Press 1/2 of the mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Top with nuts.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk in double boiler.
Pour over cake.
Pour chocolate chips over this.
Press remaining half of cake over this.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a hot greased pan or skillet.
Will not brown as well as regular cornbread, but can be set under flame of broiler to brown.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix shortening into flour until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
Knead dough until smooth on floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter. Place biscuits lightly touching.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add the sour milk with the salt and vanilla.
Add the flour, dates and nuts.
Drop on greased baking cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: joggin' in a jug
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Line pan with 1 pie crust, save other crust for top.
Mix together sugar, eggs, flour and butter.
Add salt. Mix in cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Pour in pie shelled pan and cover with crust.
Pinch sides together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Spoon the first 5 ingredients into a 2-quart casserole dish. Stir soup, mayonnaise, soy sauce and juice together in a separate bowl until well blended.
Pour soup mixture into dish and toss to coat well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add syrup, eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Mix with spoon, do not use mixer.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into each pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cheese with milk. Add other ingredients. Pour into earthenware dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serve with potato chips.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Bake corn bread mixes according to package directions (this can be done ahead of time).
Let cool.
Crumble or break into small pieces.
Set aside.
Put giblets, plus chicken pieces, in pot and cover with water.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer until meat is cooked.
Cool meat and debone. Cut into small pieces and set aside.
Remove as much fat as you can from broth.
Strain broth and discard vegetables.
Set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook the hamburg and taco seasoning; let cool.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese; place in baking dish or rectangle serving dish. Add, in layers, the seasoned hamburg, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Serve with chips on side (take chip and dip).

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Then add raisins, nuts, cinnamon and pineapple.
Pour batter into well greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with favorite cream cheese frosting.
(I prefer Pillsbury.)

title: fijian-indian chicken or lamb curry
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Put in mustard and cumin seed.
They will pop.
Fry onion until golden brown.
Add powdered coriander, garam marsala, turmeric, chili powder and salt.
Stir constantly to fry marsala.
Add garlic and ginger and fry another few minutes. If you find it a little too dry add some water.
(Do not burn.) Put in meat; stir and cook at medium heat.
With lamb add potato when partly cooked, but with chicken add potato after about 5 minutes.
Cook the meat in its own juices.
Add water.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste and simmer another 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cilantro (optional).
Serve with boiled or steamed white rice.

title: microwave sausage casserole
directions: Place sausage in 12 x 8-inch microwavable dish.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring well after 3 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain grease.
Stir rice into mixture.
Add soups, mushrooms and pimiento.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and microwave an additional 1 to 2 minutes on High.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In a large saucepan, cook noodles.
Drain cooked noodles and toss with olive oil.
Place noodles in two 7 x 11-inch greased glass baking dishes, spreading noodles up sides of dishes.

title: macaroni ham salad
directions: Boil eggs; set aside to cool.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; rinse with cold water.
In large mixing bowl, combine salad dressing, pickle relish, dill weed, sugar and half and half; mix well.
Add ham, celery, cheese, eggs and cooled macaroni; mix well.
Chill.
When ready to serve, sprinkle chow mein noodles over top. Serves 7 to 9.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a small bowl, mix yeast and water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat as you would a cake.
Add milk and yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth.
Set in a warm place to rise until it doubles in size.
Knead again and cut into 48 balls.
Roll each ball in Coating Mixture.

title: honey cream carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Melt butter in pan or microwave.
Blend in ginger.
Add carrots, honey and sour cream.
Cook until carrots are heated.
Add almonds.
Serves 4.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold liquid. Add sherbet by teaspoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, mushrooms, green onion, celery, onion and Ro-Tel tomatoes until done.
Mix with cooked rice; layer broccoli and rice, then cheese (make two layers).
Top with cheese.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar in a 1 gallon pitcher.
Add nutmeg and finish filling pitcher with cold water.
Chill before serving.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Among
my
many recipes I found this list of 50 calorie food items and taped it on the refrigerator.

title: grape sparkling punch
directions: Mix sugar and boiling water and let cool, then add juices and cold water.
Put in freezer; stir every 10 minutes.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Makes 80 servings (2 1/2 gallons).

title: texas potatoes(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes and melted butter.
Top with the corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: honey fruit dressing
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, mustard, paprika, celery seed and salt.
Add honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Pour oil into mixture very slowly, beating constantly.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.)
Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly and press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix egg, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Fold in 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Pour onto hot crust; bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, butter and syrup for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda. Will be foamy.
Pour mixture over corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour or more on cookie sheets.

title: gumma
directions: Bring the three cups milk to rolling boil. Pour in buttermilk and let simmer 15 minutes, lifting the curds now and then. Pour off the whey, and add raisins cooking until only a small amount of whey is left in pan is left. Add the one cup of boiling milk and simmer, finish by adding the sugar and thickening. Cook until the flour is cooked. If too thin add a little dry flour and cook some more. Pour on a platter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Then add bananas, baking soda and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs; cream well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add with buttermilk alternately, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Beat after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Bake in slightly greased and floured tube pan at 375° for 15 minutes, then decrease temperature to 350° for 30 minutes.
Let the cake remain in the pan for 5 minutes after removing from the oven.

title: vegetable kebabs
directions: On 4 skewers alternately thread vegetables, beginning and ending with cherry tomatoes.
Place in a shallow baking dish. Pour dressing over vegetables.
Chill until ready to serve, turning occasionally to flavor evenly.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in pieces, discard tip of wing or can use other pieces of chicken, e.g., thighs and legs.
Beat one egg. Season flour with salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg, then in flour.
Deep fry until golden brown, remove from grease, drain and place in casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Do not cover.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or so.
This is good.

title: basic quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and vegetables on pie shell.
Beat together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over cheese and vegetables.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until knife inserted near center comes out clean, almost 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop batter by tablespoons into deep fryer; fry until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towel and serve warm.

title: hot crab spread #1
directions: Break up crabmeat; sprinkle with lemon juice and mix thoroughly with cream cheese, grated onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Season with curry to taste; spoon into heat and serve dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with almonds and broil until almonds are browned.
Serve with crackers.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Finely chop potatoes.
Dry with paper towels.
Mix eggs, flour, onion and potatoes.
Make into a dough.
Heat approximately 2 tablespoons oil in pan on medium heat.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of potato mixture in pan and fry on both sides until light brown.
Serve with applesauce or other fruit.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Open the 3 cans of biscuits.
Divide each biscuit into 3 parts. Roll each part into a little ball.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon. Roll each ball in sugar-cinnamon combination; put in a Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Melt margarine and stir in remaining sugar-cinnamon and the brown sugar.
Pour over balls in pan.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into bite sized squares.
Cover with water and cook; drain.
Add butter, onions, soup, chowder, milk and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until soup is right consistency.
I prefer this to simmer in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over the cottage cheese and mix well. Add well drained fruit cocktail, marshmallows and the Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sift first three ingredients.
Make indentation in center, and add juice, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Mix until smooth.
Combine apples with sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Grease tube pan, put a layer of batter, then a layer of apples alternately three times, ending with apples and accumulated syrup on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cake needs no frosting.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients as listed.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) in bowl.
Add 1/2 of cheese to mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: super lasagna
directions: Prepare Creamettes lasagna according to package directions. Drain.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.
Mix well.
In 15 x 9-inch baking pan, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the remaining sauce, all of the spinach mixture, half the remaining Mozzarella, remaining lasagna and sauce.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Uncover.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with macaroni.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish.
Top with additional cheese.
Bake at 400° (uncovered) for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oyster stew florentine
directions: Saute oysters in butter, salt, pepper and m.s.g. until edges curl.
Add torn spinach leaves.
Heat until hot.
Add to the heated cream. Serves 1.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Blend in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff in separate bowl, then fold in.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Add apples, egg, vanilla and shortening.
Stir.
Bake in oblong pan 1 hour in low oven.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate and cherry bundt cake
directions: Sprinkle greased 12-cup microwave-safe Bundt pan with sugar, shaking to coat well.
Combine cake mix, 1 cup pie filling, eggs, water, oil and almond extract in large bowl; mix well.
Mix using cake package directions.
Pour into prepared pan.
Microwave on Defrost for 28 to 29 minutes or until cake tests done, rotating pan every 5 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
Drizzle glaze over cake.
Let stand for several minutes or until glaze sets.
Garnish with cherries from remaining pie filling.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix at room temperature all ingredients except pecans.
Chill for an hour; then roll in crushed or whole pecans.
Makes 2 to 3 balls.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pan; add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: celebrity broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until it just turns bright green and is tender. Drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese and 1 stick margarine in the microwave.
Melt 1 stick butter and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Place broccoli in a casserole dish.
Pour the cheese mixture over the broccoli.
Place the buttered Ritz crackers on top.
Place in the oven until bubbly hot.

title: peanut gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Cream shortening; add
sugar,
egg
and molasses.
Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Sift together again.
Combine ingredients.	Add milk in gradually as you combine
the
shortening
and flour mixtures, mixing well. Add peanuts
last,	reserving two tablespoons to sprinkle over top.
Bake for 20
to
minutes	in a 350° to 375° oven.
Serve warm
or
cold
with
favorite sauce.
Lemon Sauce is excellent.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Bake in greased cake pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple and cherry cobbler
directions: Mix the cherry pie filling and pineapple in a pan; pour cake mix on top of mixture evenly.
Lightly spread butter on top of cake mix.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin to dissolve.
Add marshmallows, then mayonnaise, then other ingredients.
Do not drain pineapple before adding them.
Pour into mold and let set in refrigerator until congealed.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Mix sugars and cinnamon together in bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Tumble and coat with sugar mixture.
Shake off excess and put in pan.
Place remaining sugar in a saucepan with butter and vanilla.
Melt to make a syrup. Pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out onto a plate.
Pull apart and enjoy!

title: easy bake skins
directions: Prick potatoes with fork before baking.
Bake the potatoes until soft (do not wrap in foil or grease).
Scoop out almost all of the potato, but leave a little on the peel.
(If you leave too much, they will not be crisp.)

title: meatballs
directions: Mix onions, salt, pepper, bread and milk into hamburger. Shape into balls and place in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl. Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and egg. Add milk and flour alternately. Put into a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Roll breasts in margarine and oil mixture, then in mixture of Parmesan, bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Pour 1/2 cup hot water into a 9 x9-inch glass casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.
(Wonderful when served with garlic sour cream noodles.) Serves 6.

title: mozzarella bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line baking sheet or pie plate with foil.
Set aside.
With serrated knife, cut bread into 12 wedges, being careful not to cut all the way through bottom crust.
Place loaf on baking sheet.
Brush cut side of wedges with Italian dressing.
Place cheese and peppers between slices, dividing evenly.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: In small dish, melt jello in hot water and set aside.
Dump cake mix in bowl, add cooking oil and eggs.
Add cooled jello mixture and lemon flavoring.
Mix well and bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: honey-gingered pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine honey and next 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over tenderloin. Cover and marinate in refrigerate 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: baked beans with franks
directions: Pour beans into greased baking dish.
Blend together other ingredients and pour over beans.
Place frankfurters on top and bake in moderately slow oven at 325° about 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with one cup or more grated cheese.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add blueberries and crushed pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put in pan and bring to a good boil the water, crushed pineapple and jello.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese to hot jello mixture and stir until cream cheese is dissolved.
Put in dish and refrigerate until partially set.
Prepare Dream Whip according to instructions on package and fold into jello mixture when partially set.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and heat slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove spices and serve hot.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In blender add first 4 ingredients and blend until smooth. Pour into bowl and fold in Cool Whip.
Place in pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with broken, frozen peanut butter cup.

title: ice cream sundae cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions for 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven; immediately place heaping tablespoonfuls of fudge topping on cake.
Let stand 15 minutes or until fudge topping is soft enough to spread evenly over cake. Serve slightly warm or cool with scoops of ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple chunks with juice in casserole.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese; spread over pineapple.
Melt margarine; mix with crackers.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: almond toffee
directions: Melt butter over low heat in 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Add nuts and sugar.
Turn heat to high and stir rapidly until color changes to a light caramel, about 5 minutes.
Almonds will start to pop at this stage and mixture will have a compact appearance yet be fluid enough to pour out.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and pour at once into a slightly warm ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread out as thinly and evenly as possible (about 3/8-inch thickness, candy may not fill pan completely).
Distribute chocolate chips over hot candy and spread evenly when melted.

title: squash souffle
directions: Thaw squash in pan with butter.
Mix in sugar and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add in milk.
Mix well.
Add a dash of nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: robbie's favorite fried chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in large kettle and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer about 1 hour until tender.

title: duffie's game burgers
directions: Mix ingredients and
make into patties; cook on outdoor grill.

title: quick salmon pie
directions: Clean salmon by picking out bones and skin.
Put in greased pie plate.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese and onions over it.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour over salmon.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.

title: almond raspberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop almonds very finely.
Place cookie dough in 2-quart batter bowl.
Add almonds and almond extract.
Mix with bamboo spoon to combine.
Using small stainless steel scoop, place dough 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Press lightly floured finger in center of dough to make indentation.
Fill with approximately 1/2 teaspoon raspberry preserves.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until cookie is golden brown.
Place cookies on a nonstick cooling rack.
Place powdered sugar in a flour/sugar shaker and shake over cookies until completely covered.
Yield: approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Mix well and pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: easy bread(bread machine)
directions: Put ingredients into bread machine in order given.
Select Basic cycle.
Use light or medium crust color.
Do Not use Delayed Cycle.
Makes 1 1/2 pound loaf.

title: golden pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg.
Beat until crumbly.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until set; cool.
Cut into bars. Garnish as desired.
Store tightly covered.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Saute onion and okra in the drippings about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Season chicken
with
salt
and pepper, brown chicken in additional oil or drippings in heavy skillet on low flame.
Pour off excess oil.
Add
the okra, onion mixture and gradually stir in water.
Season
with gumbo filet if desired. Cook over low heat until
chicken
is tender (about 45 minutes or more).
Remove bones
from chicken, if desired.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat; remove grease in pan. Add celery and onion and cook until tender.
In casserole, layer over half of the noodles, meat mixture, soup, tomatoes and cheese. Repeat, making another layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: light as a feather dumplings
directions: Break eggs into a measuring cup and fill with milk until it is 3/4 full.
Beat the eggs and milk together.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into simmering stock. Simmer 3 minutes on other side.
Serve at once.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: trailway cookies
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° to 325° until light brown.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix last three ingredients well; pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: broiled salmon steaks
directions: Melt butter and combine with lemon juice and spices.
Brush on salmon steaks.
Broil each steak for approximately 15 minutes (time is dependent on size of steak), turning at least once.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar. Form into balls.
Place on tray; put in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
In double boiler, melt chocolate bar, paraffin and chocolate chips.
Stick toothpicks in balls and dip into chocolate.
Place on foil to cool.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice until golden.
Butter casserole.
Add rice mixture and soups.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Before done, stir.

title: vegetable bundles
directions: Cut 4 (18 x 12-inch) pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil; coat with cooking spray.
Place squash evenly in center of each; top with onion and tomato slices.
Combine vinegar and next 3 ingredients; drizzle evenly over vegetable bundles.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese and seal securely.
Bake on a baking sheet at 400° for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
4 servings (50 calories, 18% from fat, per serving).

title: stuffed green peppers for microwave
directions: Cut 1/2 inch from stem end of peppers; set ends aside.
Remove ribs and seeds from peppers.
Place 1/4 cup water in a 2-quart microwaveproof casserole and place peppers upside down in the water.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap, turned back slightly on one side.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, or until peppers are tender-crisp.
Remove peppers;
drain and cool while preparing the stuffing.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken and remove skin.
Dredge chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry chicken until brown.
Slice up a pound of the link sausage.
After chicken is browned, place sausage in same skillet.
Use a heavy iron one.
Brown sausage on both sides.
Save the grease from chicken and sausage.
Fry tomato, onion and okra in about 2 tablespoons oil or shortening until tender.
Make a roux with 2 teaspoons oil and 2 teaspoons flour.
Stir and brown over a medium-low heat until roux is as dark as possible without burning it!
Place chicken and sausage in roux and stir.
Place all ingredients into a heavy, deep iron pan.
Add water and cook 2 hours.
Cook slow; add water, if needed.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, egg and butter. Mix on low speed of electric mixer until well blended. Slowly add flour until mixed well. Mixture will be runny. Fill greased muffin tins half full. Bake for 20 minutes or until brown. Mixture will keep in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Stir well each time before using. Yield: 24 to 36 rolls.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Spread 16 ounces sour cream on top. Dip Doritos or Fritos.

title: five cup cookies
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter, gradually add dry milk powder and sugar.
Mix well and add raisins.
Roll in small balls or long roll and slice when chilled or pack in pan and cut into squares when chilled.

title: gingerbread house dough
directions: Cream shortening.
Beat in sugar.
Add molasses.
Add water alternately with dry ingredients.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut pieces for house from dough. Transfer to cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.
Construct house.
Frost and decorate with candies.
Let your imagination be your guide.

title: arrabiato tomato sauce
directions: Coat frying pan with olive oil.
Add 2 to 3 crushed or minced garlic cloves.
Add minced 1/2 an onion, then add optional hot pepper.
Saute, then add the whole peeled tomatoes and the tomato paste.
Add fresh basil to taste and oregano to taste.
Sprinkle some black pepper if desired.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Churn in ice cream maker.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients all together; set aside.
Mix together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add the pumpkin and mix well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix until you have a smooth batter.
Add nuts.

title: johnny cake
directions: Dissolve soda in a little warm water and add to buttermilk; then add sugar and salt.
Mix and beat all together as quickly as possible.
Bake in hot, greased 9 X 14 pan in hot oven about 20 minutes.
Note:
Cost, including
stove heat = $0.0607 in 1917 terms.
From Telegram Conservation Cook Book, page 62.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be made the day before.

title: deep dish taco
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and water; put into 12 x 8-inch pan, bake 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger with green pepper and onion; drain off grease.
Stir in tomato sauce and all of your seasonings; spoon over warm crust.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large stockpot, cover hen with water and add seasonings. Cook slowly and leave in the stock until cold. Cut meat off bones in large pieces. Cook spaghetti in remaining stock.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in a casserole dish. Garnish with slivered almonds and crushed corn flakes. Bake 30 minutes at 350 in oven. Can be prepared ahead of time and baked at the last minute.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic, tomato paste, stewed tomatoes and all of the seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: bilge burner
directions: Makes gallon.
Careful, it will creep up on you fast!
See ya at the JIB.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lancaster county lima beans
directions: Boil beans nearly soft, then add potatoes.
Cook until both are soft.
Drain and add milk and butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
This makes a very good dish and the cost is low.
Serves 12.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of butter together and press into bottom of pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of butter.
Beat together for 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread onto graham cracker mixture.
Slice bananas on top.
Spread drained pineapple on top of mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top of that. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Lay cherries on top and chill.

title: zucchini crabcakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into balls or patties.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until done.
Cook onions until tender.
Drain.
Drain everything real good and mix together.
Put in 2-quart casserole and cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: waffles perfect
directions: Blend 1 cup water, vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Then add rest of ingredients to blender and blend until smooth.
Spray waffle iron generously with nonstick spray.
Pour batter on hot griddle, being sure to pour all the way to edges.
Bake 12 minutes or until steaming stops.
Add more water to batter if it gets too thick. Freezes well to be reheated in toaster or oven.
Very filling!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar and ReaLemon with mayonnaise to cover other ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine raw peanuts, sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir.
Microwave for 3 to 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: cheesy-broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in margarine.
Cook broccoli until tender; mix all ingredients with cubed cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Serve in pita bread.

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute meat until browned.
Drain.
Add onion soup mix.
Add rice to meat mixture.
Put cabbage in a large baking pan.
Spread meat mixture over cabbage.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat mixture.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand 5 minutes, then add soda.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Alternately add flour and date mixture in creamed ingredients.
Then add vanilla and nuts. Bake in greased and floured large loaf pan until done, about 1 hour at 350° or 2 small loaves for 40 minutes.

title: empanadas(ecuadorian meat turnover)
directions: Mix eggs and oil together.
Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups warm water with salt dissolved in it. Put this with flour mixture.
See if you need more flour or more water.
Let rise for at least 15 minutes.
Cover with a towel. Meanwhile, brown hamburger meat and onions.
Drain.
Cook carrots.
Mix with ground meat and onions.
Cheese can be used separately in empanadas if desired.
Roll out dough and cut into "turnover" size.
Fill with a tablespoon or so of meat mixture. Seal edge with crimped design or press with fork tines.
Fry in cooking oil.
Turn when browned, being careful not to open up and spill filling.
Ready when completely golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and shred potatoes in gallon of water.
Add salt.
Drain and wash well.
Pour yams in baking dish. Add sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook until syrup.
Add butter. Pour pineapple juice over potatoes.
Pour syrup over potatoes. Cook in oven 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat.
Place in casserole dish.
Heat first 3 ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick, buttermilk and oleo.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line pan with peaches.
Mix sugar and water.
Pour over peaches.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Put in meat loaf pan and spread with mixture of ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.
Excellent the next day for sandwiches.

title: fresh soft-serve banana ice cream
directions: Slice bananas and freeze in a single layer for several hours until firm.
If not ready to use, put in a freezer bag.
Keep no more than a couple of days.
When ready to serve, put frozen bananas in food processor until chopped and grainy but still frozen.
Add milk, a little at a time and process until smooth and creamy like frozen custard.
Do not add too much milk or process too long or mixture will become too soft.
You may add a little confectioners sugar while processing, if you desire; 95 calories per serving.
Yields 3 servings.
Eat immediately after making.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet; drain fat.
Mix tomato soup, mushroom soup, taco seasoning and milk; add to meat.
In a casserole, place a layer of tortilla pieces, then a layer of meat mixture and then a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; add other ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Roll each ball in confectioners sugar.
Makes 75 to 100.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in casserole dish. Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is thick and brown.

title: crisp little lemon cookies("easy as pie" cookies!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place on ungreased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown around edges.
Cool 1 minute and remove from sheets.
Mmm!
Even better when iced with lemon frosting!

title: pat's zucchini bars
directions: Cream eggs & sugar.
Add oil & mix in zucchini.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon mixing well.
Stir in coconut & nuts.
Grease 9 X 13 pans (2).
Divide dough between 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tested done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In saucepan, add the Karo syrup, water and sugar.
Using a candy thermometer, heat the ingredients to 270°.
Add the peanuts and continue heating to 300°.
Remove from heat and add the butter and vanilla.
Then add the baking soda and salt, stirring and pouring quickly onto the greased cookie sheets.

title: sue's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onions, mushrooms and green pepper. Pour off grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer with lid off for 1 1/2 hours (if you can wait!).

title: ham salad spread
directions: Put salad dressing, Worcestershire sauce and cut up pickle in blender and run on low until smooth.
Add ham and run on high until ham is chopped.
If necessary, stop blender and push ingredients towards blades with rubber spatula so all is mixed.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/2 cup canned milk in double boiler.
