Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 cup canned milk.
Spread 1/2 the batter in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Spread caramel mixture over all.
Put rest of cake batter on top in spoonfuls. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water; mix and cool.
Mix the cake mix, oil and eggs (one at a time); mix well.
Blend in cooled Jell-O.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for another 30 minutes.
While cake is still hot, prick with a fork.

title: wheat salad
directions: Pour 3/4 cup water over wheat, let set for 20 minutes, then drain.
Add all other ingredients and let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups grated unpeeled zucchini (dry between paper towels).
Add onion, cheese, flour, eggs, mayonnaise and spices.
Melt 1 teaspoon butter (or coat with oil) in a 10-inch skillet.
Spoon 2 heaping tablespoons of batter for each patty. Flatten with spatula.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Serve plain or with tomato sauce or grated cheese.

title: pound cake dessert
directions: Slice the pound cake and line the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch pan. Make the pudding as directed on the box.
Pour over the pound cake.
Spread the pudding until it covers all the cake. Spread the drained, crushed pineapple over the pudding and top with Cool Whip. Serve.

title: kasha and mushrooms
directions: In a small bowl, mix grouts with egg until each grout is well coated with egg.
Place in medium size saucepan over moderately high heat, and stir constantly with a wooden spoon until grouts separate and the egg begins to dry.
Remove from heat and pour boiling chicken stock or water over kasha.
Add salt and stir. Cover tightly and cook over low heat at a bare simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, or until all the liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and reserve.

title: corn dodgers
directions: Mix with cold water into a stiff mixture.
Heat and grease pan, using regular oil.
Make dough into oval ball shapes and bake until brown in 350° to 400° preheated oven.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add celery, onion and sweet pickle.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Mix all these ingredients well and add to the macaroni mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keep well for up to a week.

title: crab moose
directions: Chop (finely) celery and onion.
Sprinkle lemon juice over crab meat.
Heat cream cheese and soup until warm; do not allow to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 tablespoon cold water and combine with soup mixture to heat.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with no stick cooking spray. Press dough on pizza pan and bake according to directions on package.

Let cool. Spread cream cheese on cookie dough; spread on pineapple, arrange orange slices on pineapple, chop cherries and arrange between oranges and pineapple. Just before serving, place bananas between cherries and pineapple. Cherry pie filling may be used instead of strawberry.

title: delicate punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice trays and freeze into cubes.
When ready to serve, just drop 2 or 3 cubes into a glass and fill with ginger ale.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together egg, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: bisquick skillet meat loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; save 1/2 cup for later. Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, except potatoes, 1/2 cup bouillon, cheese and mushrooms.
Pat the meat loaf into a 9-inch skillet to within 1-inch of the edge.
Pour remaining bouillon around the edge.
Place potatoes on meat loaf in a spoke fashion.
Cover with a tight fitting lid or foil and a lid.
Cook on low heat on top of the stove (not in the oven) 40 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Then arrange the cheese and mushrooms on top of the potatoes; continue cooking until cheese is melted.

title: all-day chicken cassoulet
directions: Cook beans until tender; drain.
Cover and chill overnight. Place chicken pieces in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown pieces of chicken in skillet sprayed with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Add vegetables, salt and spices.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to skillet, stirring until gravy thickens.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Melt oleo and shortening.
Add sugars and mix.
Beat in eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and make into roll.
Place in refrigerator and slice thinly.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: dried apple substitute
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar; pour over apples.
Add a small amount of water if needed to help dissolve sugar and start apples cooking.
Cook until liquid is thick and bubbly.
Cool.
Put in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: homemade banana pudding
directions: Slowly bring milk, sugar, eggs and vanilla to a soft boil. Have your bananas sliced and layered with wafers.
Pour pudding over top.
Tastes great warm!

title: ginger cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, beat sugar and add egg (beating well).
Add flour mixture. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll dough in balls and dip in granulated sugar to coat.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cheese wedges(makes 2 cups)
directions: Combine cheese, sour cream and butter; beat until smooth. Stir in chiles and pimiento.
Spread on fresh flour tortillas. Top with another flour tortilla to make sandwich.
Cut in wedges and serve with salsa or guacamole.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients in greased casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Slice zucchini and onions; cover with water and add salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Pour over slices and let stand 2 hours, then bring syrup and zucchini slices to a boil for 3 minutes.
Process 5 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 3 pints; double recipe makes 3 quarts.

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: Cut onion, celery and green pepper into small dice.
Coarsely grate carrots.
Add to ground meats, along with ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, eggs, salt, black pepper, chili powder, mustard, paprika, horseradish and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well by using your hands.

title: easy harvest fruit and nut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with the walnuts.
Mix fruit and apples together.
Mix together and put in pie shells.
Butter pats are laid on top of the filling.
If you use a solid top crust, be sure to add slits to allow the steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel snappers
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
On it, arrange pecans, flat side down, in a group of four.
Place one caramel on each cluster of pecans. Heat in a 325° oven, about 4 to 8 minutes or until caramels soften.
(Watch carefully; various caramels melt at different rates.)
Remove from oven.
With buttered spatula, flatten caramel over pecans.
Cool slightly; remove from pan to waxed paper. Swirl melted chocolate on top.
Makes 36.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and egg.
Add pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in shallow dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fred harvey cole slaw
directions: Stir together cabbage, onion, green pepper and 1 cup sugar. Bring to a boil the salad oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Immediately pour this hot mixture over the cabbage mixture.
Chill overnight.
Store in fridge.
Keeps well up to 9 days.

title: iva's lasagne
directions: Cook ground chuck beef; drain.
Cook lasagne noodles and shred cheeses.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish first layer sauce, noodles, sauce, meat, shredded cheeses and cottage cheese; repeat layering. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: Make peanut butter and jelly sandwich.
Dip both sides in egg/milk mixture.
Cook on buttered griddle until brown on one side, then turn over and brown other side.
Eat with a knife and fork.

title: salsa
directions: Cook all ingredients 1 1/2 hours.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Saute onions, garlic and bell pepper in butter in large pot. Add tomato sauce, 2 cans water, shrimp and Creole seasoning. Simmer 1 hour.
Thicken with cornstarch and serve over rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the pie filling in a shallow baking dish.
In a bowl, combine the flour, oats, sugar, salt and spices.
Add butter; mix well.
Spread the topping evenly over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar;
add eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture with milk, food coloring, and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased tube pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and break stems from mushrooms.
Combine rice and soup. Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on a well-greased baking pan.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: moose meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl combine meat, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
In large skillet brown meatballs in oil.
Cover and cook over low heat until done, approximately 10 minutes.
In saucepan, stir vinegar and remaining cornstarch until smooth.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set pineapple aside. Add enough water to juice to equal 1 1/2 cups; stir into vinegar mixture.
Add sugar and soy sauce; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper; cook until heated through and green pepper is tender.
Serve over noodles.
Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread enough precooked fresh broccoli to cover bottom.
Over layer of broccoli, arrange chicken breasts in single layer.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and garlic powder to taste.
Spoon over the meat and broccoli. Sprinkle grated Cheddar or American cheese over sauce.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: roast boneless loin of pork
directions: Season pork with salt and pepper.
Lightly dredge in flour. Place fat side up in roasting pan.
Add vegetables, seasonings and water.
Cook at 425° for 30 minutes or until meat is well browned. Reduce heat to 325° and cook 30 minutes more, basting frequently. Add more water if necessary.
Continue cooking and basting 45 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 180° on meat thermometer.
Remove to platter.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut flank steak into 1/4-inch thick strips with grain.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.
Place strips flat on rack over foil and bake in 150° oven for 3 hours.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, salt, pepper and sugar.
Drain well.
Add tomato soup.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture in a casserole dish with cheese between layers and on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Add soup and onions.
Mix with 3/4 cup cheese and save remaining for top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hungry man's baked beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place bacon (raw) on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in Dutch oven. (This will fill a Dutch oven.)

title: better than sex
directions: With an electric mixer, combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and water.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix again. Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Spoon in batter and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine with other ingredients (except bread crumbs).
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs (plain or toast).
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick minestrone
directions: In a 5-quart kettle or Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium heat until it begins to brown.
Mix in onion, mushrooms, garlic and carrots.
Cook, stirring until onion is soft.
Add broth, tomatoes (coarsely chopped with liquid), salt, basil, thyme and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Bring soup to boiling; add pasta.
Bring again to boiling and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until nearly tender, about 10 minutes.
Add peas and parsley and boil for 2 minutes.
Taste; add salt, if needed.
Serve with cheese to add to taste.

title: chemical garden
directions: Mix bluing, water and salt.
Add ammonia.
Mix well and pour slowly over 3 or 4 small rocks, clinkers or coal in an old pie pan.
Crystals start to grow very soon and will continue as long as the liquid stays.
If you want a little color, add a few drops of food coloring to the rocks.
Set the pan where you can watch it daily.

title: spinach-orange salad
directions: Combine spinach and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently.
Serve with Yogurt-Poppy Seed Dressing.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 58 calories (6% from fat) per serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spray Pam in cake pan.
Cook equivalent of whole chicken or about 10 boneless breasts. Cut into small pieces. Line bottom of pan with it.
Cook frozen broccoli cuts. Spread over cooked chicken. Cover broccoli with Velveeta cheese slices. Cover cheese with cream of celery or cream of mushroom soup.

title: stuffed franks
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package.
Add cheese, pepper and salt to taste. Steam franks until puffed.
Slit lengthwise and fill with potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg; add soda to buttermilk and add to egg.
Mix in flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add melted shortening. Pour in preheated and oiled skillet.
Bake at 475° until slightly browned.

title: oriental chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan or skillet.
Add garlic and onion; cook a few minutes.
Stir in tomato soup, water, brown sugar, salt and chili powder, mixing well.
Add beans with juice and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients and heat about 5 minutes.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Open biscuits; flatten slightly and arrange around outside edges of dish on top of mixture, overlapping if necessary.
Brush biscuits with melted butter; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, until biscuits brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and divide into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Drain cherries and keep 1/4 cup red syrup only.
Place 2 circles peaches around outer edge of pizza crust.
Then 1 circle red cherries, 1 circle green cherries, 1 circle pineapple chunks, 1 circle nuts and raisins in center.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Combine, mixing well, and let stand at least 24 hours to ripen.
Before using, mix twice.
Keep in refrigerator, covered well.
Will keep quite a few days.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix
and put mixture into peppers. Put tomato soup over peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon salt on cabbage, cover and set in refrigerator one hour.

title: creamy spam and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with vegetable cooking spray.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In casserole, combine macaroni, broccoli, Spam and red pepper.
In small saucepan, stir together milk, cornstarch and pepper until cornstarch is dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine sauce with other ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup; level off and pour measured flour onto waxed paper.
Add soda and salt to flour.
Stir to blend. Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop by teaspoonfuls or shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's as desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: potato salad(classic mayonnaise recipe)
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and flavoring.
Make paste of cocoa and coloring and add.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk. Mix soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Blend.
Bake in a 9 or 10-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, mash bananas (a potato masher works great.) Add remaining ingredients, mixing as you go. Pour into one non-stick or lightly greased loaf pan. You may also use 4 mini-loaf pans.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: In blender, puree strawberries and 1 cup of the water.
In a pitcher, combine pureed strawberries, remaining 2 cups of water, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill. Just before serving, add the club soda and pour over ice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and buttermilk.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine spinach with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet and freeze.
When frozen, remove from sheet and place in plastic freezer bags.
Keep frozen until ready to use.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash, drain and slice cucumbers and onions. Add garlic and salt.
Mix well.
Cover with ice cubes and let stand 3 hours. Drain well.
Remove garlic. Combine remaining ingredients in a large saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add cucumbers and heat for 5 minutes.
Pack loosely in hot canning jars.
Process for 5 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool 10 minutes. Add cranberry sauce.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir sour cream and add to Jell-O and cranberries.
Mix well.
Pour into a mold and chill.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: joe's spicy black-eyed peas(serves 6)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble; save.
Stir remaining ingredients into bacon grease in skillet and cook. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into serving dish.
Sprinkle bacon and parsley over.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Cook and drain meat. Add other ingredients. Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place all Tater Tots in a greased, oblong pan in a single layer.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and cheese.
Pour mixture evenly over Tater Tots.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until heated completely through and bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and pumpkin for 3 minutes, then add dry ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Fill 3 loaf pans half full.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or cream cheese.

title: cherry cream cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add milk; beat well. Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well. Pour filling into crust. Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Top with cherry pie filling. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin, eggs, sugar and spices in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour in milk and fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place butter, cocoa and water into saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add to flour and sugar right away.
Then add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into an 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove.
In an additional 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated; stir often.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Toss until well mixed.
Place in small (8-inch) buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(Mixture bakes into torte-like pie.)
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix together and form in half-moon shapes.
Cook in 350° oven.

title: elephant stew
directions: You will need a large bowl and 10 to 12 canoe paddles.

title: hot seafood casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of crumbs in pan.
Place remainder on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Double this recipe for 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugars.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add to the sugar mixture.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the mixture with the milk.
Chill until ready to use.
Take small chilled balls and mash on a cookie sheet.
Add nuts, chocolate chips, raisins, anything you want.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Keeps in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, whip cream cheese, ham and mustard.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and chives.
Shape into a ball, chilling beforehand, if necessary.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: funeral beans
directions: Mix beans with sauce or soup in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake until heated thoroughly.

title: chicken rotini macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Continue baking until melted. Seve hot or cold.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well and drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Criss cross cookies with fork on cookies.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots 1/4-inch thick and soak in salt water for 5 minutes (boiling water).
Drain, cool and set aside.
In blender, combine soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce. Blend quickly.
Place carrots, pepper and onion in a bowl and pour mixture over top.
Refrigerate.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Combine flour with seasonings; coat chicken lightly with mixture.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until fork-tender.

title: tart green beans with bacon
directions: Wash, cut off ends and cut green beans into crosswise pieces. Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender (frozen or canned green beans may be substituted for fresh beans.
Follow directions on package or container for cooking.)

title: soup
directions: Put beans, onion and celery in the water.
Boil 30 minutes. Blend in food processor.
Puree tomatoes and add to soup.
Stir in chili sauce and seasonings.
Melt butter.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes.
Stir into the soup over medium heat until soup thickens.

title: puree of carrot soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the oil and add the carrots, onion, celery, potatoes, garlic and sugar.
Cover the pan and cook the vegetables over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring them occasionally.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Mix seasonings well.
Rub mixture on the meat.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, uncovered.

title: piggybank pork bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in noodles, soup, corn (with liquid), pimento, cheese and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: microwave no bake chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa powder and stir in milk.
Stir in butter and corn syrup.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 3 to 4 minutes or until mix is boiling rapidly, stirring once.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 3 more minutes, stirring every minute.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until boiling.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Beat for 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Drop teaspoonful on wax paper.
Cool.

title: banana punch
directions: Stir together.
On the stove heat 3 cups water and 3 cups sugar until dissolved, then cool.
Mix 5 to 6 ripe bananas.
Add a little to pineapple mixture from above in a blender until smooth.
Mix all together and freeze.
Set out until slushy and add 2 quarts of 7-Up when ready to serve.
Serves about 50 people.

title: chillin out pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain and cool.
In a large bowl, stir together yogurt, mustard and herb seasoning.
Add pasta, celery and green onion.
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: garlic and potato soup
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day, preheat oven to 350°.
Remove any loose papery skin from garlic, leaving head intact.
Place garlic in small baking dish.
Pour olive or salad oil over garlic. Cover and bake garlic 1 hour. Cool garlic until easy to handle. Separate garlic head into cloves.
Press soft, cooked garlic from each clove into small bowl. Discard skin. Reserve 1 tablespoon olive or salad oil from roasted garlic.

title: creamed chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Put onion, celery and margarine in frying pan. Saute until limp. Add noodles and rest of ingredients. Put in large casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until hot.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles; heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add flour; cook for a few minutes stirring.
Add pepper, salt and slowly stir in broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer until slightly thickened.
Stir in cream, chicken and cheese.
Heat butter and lemon juice.
Saute mushrooms.
Drain noodles, combine with cream mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Spread mushrooms and more cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: massachusettes biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt with a fork.
With a pastry bender, cut butter or margarine into the mixture until it is crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat milk and egg with a fork.
Stir into flour mixture just until all of the flour is moistened.
Place dough on a lightly-floured board or counter top and knead gently for 5 or 6 times with a rolling pin.
Roll into a 9-inch circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425° or until golden brown.

title: crock-potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan and add sour cream and soup until hot. Combine with cooked and sliced potatoes in crock-pot on low.
Heat for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!
This may also be baked in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: turtles
directions: Heat caramels and water in double boiler; stir until melted. Grease baking sheet.
Arrange 36 groups of 4 nuts, 2-inches apart. Drop caramel by teaspoonfuls.
Let turtle cool 15 minutes. (Reheat caramel, if necessary.)
Melt chocolate chips over hot, not boiling water.
Drop by teaspoons on each turtle.
Makes 36.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Brown onion in butter or margarine.
Place in bowl with meat, breadcrumbs, eggs, seasonings and blend well.
Shape into bite-size balls; roll in flour; fry until done.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll out.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: little debbie cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and
eggs.
Add the rest of ingredients. Roll into small balls and flatten on cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.
When cool, put two cookies together with filling.

title: rice krispies cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and red pepper. Add Rice Krispies.
Mix all well.
Roll into balls or drop by teaspoonfuls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake about 12 minutes or until lightly browned at 375°.

title: strawberry jello whip pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
(Store leftover pie in refrigerator.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: herbed garlic cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and seasoning until well blended. Cover and refrigerate
for at least two hours. Serve with crackers.

title: mardel's homemade cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and milk and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; beat for 2 1/2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool about 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Churn like regular ice cream. Delicious.
Enjoy.

title: veggie bites
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, green onions, peppers and olives may be used ( about 1
cup each or to taste).

title: pickled garlic
directions: In a 2-quart non-aluminum pan, combine vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Drop garlic into boiling mixture and cook uncovered for 1 minute over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; cool.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter and flour.
Chill in refrigerator.
Mold to small muffin tin.
Mix the brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla, salt and pecans together.
Place this in crust and bake at 325° for 25 minutes, until filling is set.

title: american chop suey ii
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Meanwhile cook hamburg in frying pan.
Cook in bacon fat until tender, green pepper, onion and celery.
Add tomatoes.
Strain noodles.
Return to pan and add vegetables.
When heating for the next day, add a little milk if dry.
Serves 6 good helpings.

title: sausage rounds appetizer
directions: Cook beef and sausage in frypan until done. Sprinkle in some garlic and onion powder, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well. Cut up cheese and add to meat. Cook until it melts.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to use. Spread on rye party bread.
Put on cookie sheet and broil 2 to 5 minutes.

title: delao's nopales(cactus)
directions: Cut 4 nopales; put them flat on a cutting board.
Scrape both sides until you remove all stickers.
Rinse them, dice them in small pieces and cook them in 2 cups of boiling water with salt for 10 minutes.
Remove them; let them cool off.
Rinse them in cool water; fry them in oil and scramble them with onions and eggs and spice them up.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift first 4 items; add to rest of ingredients which have been mixed together.
Bake at 360° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: shaker wheaten bread
directions: Scald milk; add salt, butter, syrup and 3/4 cup of warm water. Stir well.
Let cool to lukewarm.
In the remaining 1/4 cup water, dissolve the yeast; add to other mixture.
Add flour gradually and knead into a smooth ball.
Place in buttered bowl and brush top with soft butter.
Let rise to double its bulk. Knead lightly this time and shape into loaf in pan.
Again brush with soft butter and let rise to twice its bulk.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken one-dish meal
directions: Simmer chicken in salt water with bay leaf until tender, about 2 hours.
Remove chicken from broth and strip meat from bones. Cook rice, using chicken broth instead of water.
Saute onion and celery in margarine, then add to rice, broccoli, chicken and pepper.
Mix well and place in casserole.
Combine cheese and soup in small saucepan, heat until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken mixture and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fancy applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add hot applesauce with baking soda; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well. Fold in raisins, nuts and cherries.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° oven.
When cool, wrap in wine cloth and store in tight container.
Stays moist for weeks.
Let stand about a week or 10 days before eating for full flavor.

title: boil-bake country ham
directions: Three
days
before
serving, in large roaster or stock pot, soak ham overnight in enough cold water to cover.
In the morning remove ham, place in sink and scrub with a brush under running water
until
it
has
been
cleaned
of any cleaning debris. Wash
roaster,
place
ham
in
it
and cover it with water.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of brown sugar to ham water and bring
to
boil, immediately reducing heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes
per
pound for older ham, 15 to 18 minutes for quick-aged
ham,
or
until the small bone in hock can be pulled out with the fingers.
Let cool in cooking water overnight.

title: pecan rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on the package.
In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender, but not browned. Add hot cooked rice, pecans, parsley, basil, ginger, salt and pepper.
Mix well by lifting with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Pour water over dates.
Let stand until rest is ready.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs, salt, flour and soda, then add dates.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or longer in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; keep 2 teaspoons of juice.
Add juice to all the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon by tablespoonful into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Stir in sugar and flour; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.
You may add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: blackened redfish
directions: Place fish fillets on a cutting board; trim off any thin edges and very thin tip of tail.
If left on, these thin areas will char and break away.
Pat fillets dry with paper towels; cover and refrigerate until ready to cook.
The butter sauce adheres better to cold fillets.

title: scallops nicoise
directions: Core and peel tomatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
There should be about 3 1/2 cups. Chop the olives. There should be about 3 tablespoons of the green and 1 1/2 tablespoons of the black. Saute the garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Add olives and capers, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar in a bowl, then sift in dry ingredients. Add eggs, vanilla, apples, nuts and cinnamon. Mix well. Add raisins and rum flavoring, if desired. Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kraut and wieners
directions: Saute onion and wieners in margarine.
Drain kraut and mix in onions and wieners.
Simmer with extra salt and pepper.

title: doctored beans
directions: Saute finely chopped onion in bacon fat.
Mix together everything but the beans.
Add beans.
Mix well, after draining beans and removing pieces of fat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in oven or crock-pot for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic and lemon pepper.
Crumble bacon and put into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into partly baked (about 5 minutes) pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until a knife comes out clean.

title: chicken salad to please
directions: *Note:
You may need to add more or less Miracle Whip.
It depends on your taste.
Creamier is better!

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Crush crackers, mix in sugar and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan.
In a large electric mixer bowl, beat egg whites, strawberries, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat for 20 minutes; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crust and freeze.
Let stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place apples in bowl and cover with 1 cup sugar, stirring to mix.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend remaining sugar and eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this to egg mixture.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until soft and add remaining ingredients except franks.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Add franks and simmer for 1 hour.
Transfer to crock-pot or heated chafing dish and provide wooden picks.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: In a large container, bring tomatoes, salt and pepper to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes (add 1/2 teaspoon sugar at this time).

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool with cold water.
Mix onions, cucumbers and tomatoes (after you have diced or chopped them).
Mix vegetable with noodles.
Add garlic powder and dressing.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: enchilada sauce with cheese
directions: Cook minced onion in shortening until beginning to brown.
Add the chili powder and combine.
Add tomato juice, salt and sugar; simmer for 20 minutes.
Moisten flour with cold water to thicken. Add cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve hot over fried corn meal mush.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spread ham over top of potatoes.
Spread mushroom soup over top.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over top.
Lay slices of butter or margarine over top; add 1/2 cup milk.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: red cucumber pickle
directions: Mix vinegar, red food coloring and alum.
Add enough water to cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Discard juice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine and saute carrots and onion in it.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups of stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Fold in zucchini and turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and toss remaining stuffing mix in it.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Put grated cheese on top if desired.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine
flour,
brown	sugar,	pecans	and
margarine. Press into a
9-inch
baking
pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; cool.
Crumble
crust and firmly press back into pan. Combine whipped topping mix and milk.
Whip until fluffy.
Set aside. Combine cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, powdered sugar and vanilla;
mix
well and fold into whipped topping.	Spread mixture over
crust
and
top
with pie filling.
Chill for 12 hours.
